2568  void createSymmetryConstrain(int GeoId1, Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, int GeoId2, Sketcher::PointPos PosId2, int GeoId3, Sketcher::PointPos PosId3) {
2569  if (selPoints.size() == 2 && selLine.size() == 1) {
2570  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
2571  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId3);
2572  std::swap(PosId1, PosId3);
2573  }
2574  else if (isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
2575  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
2576  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
2577  }
2578 
2579  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
2580  return;
2581  }
2582 
2583  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId3);
2584 
2585  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
2586  if (GeoId1 == GeoId2 && GeoId2 == GeoId3) {
2587  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
2588  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
2589  QObject::tr("Cannot add a symmetry constraint between a line and its end points!"));
2590  return;
2591  }
2592 
2593  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d)) ",
2594  GeoId1, static_cast<int>(PosId1), GeoId2, static_cast<int>(PosId2), GeoId3);
2595 
2596  addConstraintIndex();
2597  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
2598  }
2599  }
2600  else {
2601  if (selPoints.size() == 1 && selLine.size() == 1) { //1line 1 point
2602  if (GeoId1 == GeoId3) {
2603  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
2604  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
2605  QObject::tr("Cannot add a symmetry constraint between a line and its end points!"));
2606  return;
2607  }
2608  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
2609  return;
2610  }
2611  }
2612  else {
2613  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
2614  return;
2615  }
2616  }
2617  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d)) ",
2618  GeoId1, static_cast<int>(PosId1), GeoId2, static_cast<int>(PosId2), GeoId3, static_cast<int>(PosId3));
2619 
2620  addConstraintIndex();
2621  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
2622  }
2623  }
2624 
2625  void updateDistanceType(Base::Vector2d onSketchPos)
2626  {
2627  const std::vector< Sketcher::Constraint* >& vals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
2628  Sketcher::ConstraintType type = vals[vals.size() - 1]->Type;
2629 
2630  Base::Vector3d pnt1, pnt2;
2631  bool addedOrigin = false;
2632  if (selPoints.size() == 1) {
2633  //Case of single point selected, for distance constraint. We add temporarily the origin in the vector.
2634  addedOrigin = true;
2635  SelIdPair selIdPair;
2636  selIdPair.GeoId = Sketcher::GeoEnum::RtPnt;
2637  selIdPair.PosId = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
2638  selPoints.push_back(selIdPair);
2639  }
2640 
2641  if (selLine.size() == 1) {
2642  pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::start);
2643  pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::end);
2644  }
2645  else {
2646  pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(selPoints[0].GeoId, selPoints[0].PosId);
2647  pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(selPoints[1].GeoId, selPoints[1].PosId);
2648  }
2649 
2650  double minX, minY, maxX, maxY;
2651  minX = min(pnt1.x, pnt2.x);
2652  maxX = max(pnt1.x, pnt2.x);
2653  minY = min(pnt1.y, pnt2.y);
2654  maxY = max(pnt1.y, pnt2.y);
2655  if (onSketchPos.x > minX && onSketchPos.x < maxX
2656  && (onSketchPos.y < minY || onSketchPos.y > maxY) && type != Sketcher::DistanceX) {
2657  restartCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add DistanceX constraint"));
2658  specialConstraint = SpecialConstraint::LineOr2PointsDistance;
2659  if (selLine.size() == 1) {
2660  createDistanceXYConstrain(Sketcher::DistanceX, selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::start, selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::end, onSketchPos);
2661  }
2662  else {
2663  createDistanceXYConstrain(Sketcher::DistanceX, selPoints[0].GeoId, selPoints[0].PosId, selPoints[1].GeoId, selPoints[1].PosId, onSketchPos);
2664  }
2665  }
2666  else if (onSketchPos.y > minY && onSketchPos.y < maxY
2667  && (onSketchPos.x < minX || onSketchPos.x > maxX) && type != Sketcher::DistanceY) {
2668  restartCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add DistanceY constraint"));
2669  specialConstraint = SpecialConstraint::LineOr2PointsDistance;
2670  if (selLine.size() == 1) {
2671  createDistanceXYConstrain(Sketcher::DistanceY, selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::start, selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::end, onSketchPos);
2672  }
2673  else {
2674  createDistanceXYConstrain(Sketcher::DistanceY, selPoints[0].GeoId, selPoints[0].PosId, selPoints[1].GeoId, selPoints[1].PosId, onSketchPos);
2675  }
2676  }
2677  else if ((((onSketchPos.y < minY || onSketchPos.y > maxY) && (onSketchPos.x < minX || onSketchPos.x > maxX))
2678  || (onSketchPos.y > minY && onSketchPos.y < maxY && onSketchPos.x > minX && onSketchPos.x < maxX)) && type != Sketcher::Distance) {
2679  restartCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add Distance constraint"));
2680  if (selLine.size() == 1) {
2681  createDistanceConstrain(selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::start, selLine[0].GeoId, Sketcher::PointPos::end, onSketchPos);
2682  }
2683  else {
2684  createDistanceConstrain(selPoints[0].GeoId, selPoints[0].PosId, selPoints[1].GeoId, selPoints[1].PosId, onSketchPos);
2685  }
2686  }
2687 
2688  if (addedOrigin) {
2689  //remove origin
2690  selPoints.pop_back();
2691  }
2692  }
2693 
2694  bool isRadiusDoF(int geoId)
2695  {
2696  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(geoId);
2697  if (!isArcOfCircle(*geo)) {
2698  return false;
2699  }
2700 
2701  //make sure we are not taking into account the constraint created in previous mode.
2702  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
2703  Obj->solve();
2704 
2705  auto solvext = Obj->getSolvedSketch().getSolverExtension(geoId);
2706 
2707  if (solvext) {
2708  auto arcInfo = solvext->getArc();
2709 
2710  return !arcInfo.isRadiusDoF();
2711  }
2712 
2713  return false;
2714  }
2715 
2716  void finishDimensionCreation(int GeoId1, int GeoId2, Base::Vector2d onSketchPos)
2717  {
2718  bool fixed = GeoId2 == GeoEnum::GeoUndef ? isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1) : areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
2719 
2720  int index = Obj->Constraints.getValues().size() - 1;
2721  if (fixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
2722  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%i,%s)", index, "False");
2723  }
2724 
2725  addConstraintIndex();
2726  moveConstraint(index, onSketchPos);
2727  }
2728 
2729  void addConstraintIndex()
2730  {
2731  cstrIndexes.push_back(Obj->Constraints.getValues().size() - 1);
2732  }
2733 
2734  bool hasBeenAborted()
2735  {
2736  // User can abort the command with Undo (ctrl-Z)
2737  if (!cstrIndexes.empty()) {
2738  int lastConstrIndex = Obj->Constraints.getSize() - 1;
2739  if (cstrIndexes.back() != lastConstrIndex) {
2740  return true;
2741  }
2742  }
2743 
2744  return false;
2745  }
2746 
2747  void restartCommand(const char* cstrName) {
2748  specialConstraint = SpecialConstraint::None;
2749  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
2750  Obj->solve();
2751  sketchgui->draw(false, false); // Redraw
2752  Gui::Command::openCommand(cstrName);
2753 
2754  cstrIndexes.clear();
2755  }
2756 
2757  void resetTool()
2758  {
2759  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
2760  Gui::Selection().clearSelection();
2761  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Dimension"));
2762  cstrIndexes.clear();
2763  specialConstraint = SpecialConstraint::None;
2764  previousOnSketchPos = Base::Vector2d(0.f, 0.f);
2765  clearRefVectors();
2766  }
2767 };

2825 class CmdSketcherCompHorizontalVertical : public Gui::GroupCommand

2827 public:
2828  CmdSketcherCompHorizontalVertical()
2829  : GroupCommand("Sketcher_CompHorVer")
2830  {
2831  sAppModule = "Sketcher";
2832  sGroup = "Sketcher";
2833  sMenuText = QT_TR_NOOP("Constrain horizontal/vertical");
2834  sToolTipText = QT_TR_NOOP("Constrains a single line to either horizontal or vertical.");
2835  sWhatsThis = "Sketcher_CompHorVer";
2836  sStatusTip = sToolTipText;
2837  eType = ForEdit;
2838 
2839  setCheckable(false);
2840  setRememberLast(false);
2841 
2842  addCommand("Sketcher_ConstrainHorVer");
2843  addCommand("Sketcher_ConstrainHorizontal");
2844  addCommand("Sketcher_ConstrainVertical");
2845  }
2846 
2847  const char* className() const override
2848  {
2849  return "CmdSketcherCompHorizontalVertical";
2850  }
2851

2853  {
2854  return isCommandActive(getActiveGuiDocument());
2855  }

2858 // ============================================================================
2859 bool canHorVerBlock(Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj, int geoId)
2860 {
2861  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
2862 
2863  // check if the edge already has a Horizontal/Vertical/Block constraint
2864  for (auto& constr : vals) {
2865  if (constr->Type == Sketcher::Horizontal && constr->First == geoId
2866  && constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
2867  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
2868  Obj,
2869  QObject::tr("Double constraint"),
2870  QObject::tr("The selected edge already has a horizontal constraint!"));
2871  return false;
2872  }
2873  if (constr->Type == Sketcher::Vertical && constr->First == geoId
2874  && constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
2875  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
2876  Obj,
2877  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
2878  QObject::tr("The selected edge already has a vertical constraint!"));
2879  return false;
2880  }
2881  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
2882  if (constr->Type == Sketcher::Block && constr->First == geoId
2883  && constr->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
2884  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
2885  Obj,
2886  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
2887  QObject::tr("The selected edge already has a Block constraint!"));
2888  return false;
2889  }
2890  }
2891  return true;
2892 }
2893 
2894 void horVerActivated(CmdSketcherConstraint* cmd, std::string type)
2895 {
2896  // get the selection
2897  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = Gui::Command::getSelection().getSelectionEx();
2898 
2899  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
2900  if (selection.size() != 1
2901  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
2902  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
2903  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
2904  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
2905 
2906  if (constraintMode) {
2907  ActivateHandler(cmd->getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(cmd));
2908  Gui::Command::getSelection().clearSelection();
2909  }
2910  else {
2911  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(cmd->getActiveGuiDocument(),
2912  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
2913  QObject::tr("Select an edge from the sketch."));
2914  }
2915  return;
2916  }
2917 
2918  // get the needed lists and objects
2919  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
2920  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
2921 
2922  std::vector<int> edgegeoids;
2923  std::vector<int> pointgeoids;
2924  std::vector<Sketcher::PointPos> pointpos;
2925 
2926  int fixedpoints = 0;
2927 
2928  for (auto& name : SubNames) {
2929  int GeoId;
2930  Sketcher::PointPos PosId;
2931  getIdsFromName(name, Obj, GeoId, PosId);
2932 
2933  if (isEdge(GeoId, PosId)) {// it is an edge
2934  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
2935 
2936  if (!isLineSegment(*geo)) {
2937  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
2938  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
2939  QObject::tr("The selected edge is not a line segment."));
2940  return;
2941  }
2942 
2943  if (canHorVerBlock(Obj, GeoId)) {
2944  edgegeoids.push_back(GeoId);
2945  }
2946  }
2947  else if (isVertex(GeoId, PosId)) {
2948  // can be a point, a construction point, an external point or root
2949 
2950  if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId)) {
2951  fixedpoints++;
2952  }
2953 
2954  pointgeoids.push_back(GeoId);
2955  pointpos.push_back(PosId);
2956  }
2957  }
2958 
2959  if (edgegeoids.empty() && pointgeoids.size() < 2) {
2960  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
2961  Obj,
2962  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
2963  QObject::tr("The selected item(s) can't accept a horizontal or vertical constraint!"));
2964  return;
2965  }
2966 
2967  // if there is at least one edge selected, ignore the point alignment functionality
2968  if (!edgegeoids.empty()) {
2969  // undo command open
2970  const char* cmdName = type == "Horizontal" ? "Add horizontal constraint" : type == "Vertical" ? "Add vertical constraint" : "Add horizontal/vertical constraint";
2971  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", cmdName));
2972  for (auto& geoId : edgegeoids) {
2973  std::string typeToApply = type;
2974  if (type == "HorVer") {
2975  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(geoId);
2976  auto* line = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo);
2977  double angle = toVector2d(line->getEndPoint() - line->getStartPoint()).Angle();
2978  typeToApply = fabs(sin(angle)) < fabs(cos(angle)) ? "Horizontal" : "Vertical";
2979  }
2980 
2981  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
2982  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('%s',%d))",
2983  typeToApply,
2984  geoId);
2985  }
2986  }
2987  else if (fixedpoints <= 1) {// pointgeoids
2988  // undo command open
2989  const char* cmdName = type == "Horizontal" ? "Add horizontal alignment" : type == "Vertical" ? "Add vertical alignment" : "Add horizontal/vertical alignment";
2990  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", cmdName));
2991  std::vector<int>::iterator it;
2992  std::vector<Sketcher::PointPos>::iterator itp;
2993  for (it = pointgeoids.begin(), itp = pointpos.begin();
2994  it != std::prev(pointgeoids.end()) && itp != std::prev(pointpos.end());
2995  it++, itp++) {
2996 
2997  std::string typeToApply = type;
2998  if (type == "HorVer") {
2999  auto point1 = Obj->getPoint(*it, *itp);
3000  auto point2 = Obj->getPoint(*std::next(it), *std::next(itp));
3001  double angle = toVector2d(point2 - point1).Angle();
3002  typeToApply = fabs(sin(angle)) < fabs(cos(angle)) ? "Horizontal" : "Vertical";
3003  }
3004 
3005  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3006  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('%s',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
3007  typeToApply,
3008  *it,
3009  static_cast<int>(*itp),
3010  *std::next(it),
3011  static_cast<int>(*std::next(itp)));
3012  }
3013  }
3014  else {// vertex mode, fixedpoints > 1
3015  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
3016  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
3017  QObject::tr("There are more than one fixed points selected. "
3018  "Select a maximum of one fixed point!"));
3019  return;
3020  }
3021  // finish the transaction and update
3022  Gui::Command::commitCommand();
3023 
3024  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
3025 
3026  // clear the selection (convenience)
3027  Gui::Command::getSelection().clearSelection();
3028 }
3029 
3030 void horVerApplyConstraint(CmdSketcherConstraint* cmd, std::string type, std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
3031 {
3032  auto* sketchgui =
3033  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(cmd->getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
3034  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
3035 
3036  switch (seqIndex) {
3037  case 0:// {Edge}
3038  {
3039  if (selSeq.empty()) {
3040  return;
3041  }
3042 
3043  int CrvId = selSeq.front().GeoId;
3044  if (CrvId != -1) {
3045  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(CrvId);
3046 
3047  if (!isLineSegment(*geo)) {
3048  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
3049  Obj,
3050  QObject::tr("Impossible constraint"),
3051  QObject::tr("The selected edge is not a line segment."));
3052  return;
3053  }
3054 
3055  // check if the edge already has a Horizontal/Vertical/Block constraint
3056  if (!canHorVerBlock(Obj, CrvId)) {
3057  return;
3058  }
3059 
3060  std::string typeToApply = type;
3061  if (type == "HorVer") {
3062  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(CrvId);
3063  auto* line = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo);
3064  double angle = toVector2d(line->getEndPoint() - line->getStartPoint()).Angle();
3065  typeToApply = fabs(sin(angle)) < fabs(cos(angle)) ? "Horizontal" : "Vertical";
3066  }
3067 
3068  const char* cmdName = typeToApply == "Horizontal" ? "Add horizontal constraint" : "Add vertical constraint";
3069  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", cmdName));
3070 
3071  // issue the actual commands to create the constraint
3072  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3073  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('%s',%d))",
3074  typeToApply,
3075  CrvId);
3076  // finish the transaction and update
3077  Gui::Command::commitCommand();
3078 
3079  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
3080  }
3081 
3082  break;
3083  }
3084 
3085  case 1:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
3086  case 2:// {SelRoot, SelVertex}
3087  {
3088  int GeoId1, GeoId2;
3089  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2;
3090  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
3091  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
3092  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
3093  PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
3094 
3095  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
3096  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
3097  return;
3098  }
3099 
3100  std::string typeToApply = type;
3101  if (type == "HorVer") {
3102  auto point1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
3103  auto point2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
3104  double angle = toVector2d(point2 - point1).Angle();
3105  typeToApply = fabs(sin(angle)) < fabs(cos(angle)) ? "Horizontal" : "Vertical";
3106  }
3107 
3108  // undo command open
3109  const char* cmdName = type == "Horizontal" ? "Add horizontal alignment" : "Add vertical alignment";
3110  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", cmdName));
3111 
3112  // issue the actual commands to create the constraint
3113  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3114  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('%s',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
3115  typeToApply,
3116  GeoId1,
3117  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
3118  GeoId2,
3119  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
3120  // finish the transaction and update
3121  Gui::Command::commitCommand();
3122 
3123  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
3124 
3125  break;
3126  }
3127  }
3128 }

3301 void CmdSketcherConstrainLock::activated(int iMsg)
3302 {
3303  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
3304 
3305  // get the selection
3306  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
3307 
3308  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
3309  if (selection.size() != 1
3310  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
3311  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
3312  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
3313  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
3314 
3315  if (constraintMode) {
3316  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
3317  getSelection().clearSelection();
3318  }
3319  else {
3320  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
3321  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3322  QObject::tr("Select vertices from the sketch."));
3323  }
3324  return;
3325  }
3326 
3327  // get the needed lists and objects
3328  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
3329  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
3330 
3331  std::vector<int> GeoId;
3332  std::vector<Sketcher::PointPos> PosId;
3333 
3334  for (std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator it = SubNames.begin(); it != SubNames.end();
3335  ++it) {
3336  int GeoIdt;
3337  Sketcher::PointPos PosIdt;
3338  getIdsFromName((*it), Obj, GeoIdt, PosIdt);
3339  GeoId.push_back(GeoIdt);
3340  PosId.push_back(PosIdt);
3341 
3342  if ((it != std::prev(SubNames.end())
3343  && (isEdge(GeoIdt, PosIdt) || (GeoIdt < 0 && GeoIdt >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis)))
3344  || (it == std::prev(SubNames.end()) && isEdge(GeoIdt, PosIdt))) {
3345  if (selection.size() == 1) {
3346  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
3347  Obj,
3348  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3349  QObject::tr("Select one vertex from the sketch other than the origin."));
3350  }
3351  else {
3352  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
3353  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3354  QObject::tr("Select only vertices from the sketch. The "
3355  "last selected vertex may be the origin."));
3356  }
3357  // clear the selection (convenience)
3358  getSelection().clearSelection();
3359  return;
3360  }
3361  }
3362 
3363  int lastconstraintindex = Obj->Constraints.getSize() - 1;
3364 
3365  if (GeoId.size() == 1) {// absolute mode
3366  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
3367  bool edgeisblocked = false;
3368 
3369  if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId[0])) {
3370  edgeisblocked = true;
3371  }
3372 
3373  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(GeoId[0], PosId[0]);
3374 
3375  // undo command open
3376  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add 'Lock' constraint"));
3377  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3378  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%f))",
3379  GeoId[0],
3380  static_cast<int>(PosId[0]),
3381  pnt.x);
3382  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3383  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%f))",
3384  GeoId[0],
3385  static_cast<int>(PosId[0]),
3386  pnt.y);
3387 
3388  lastconstraintindex += 2;
3389 
3390  if (edgeisblocked || GeoId[0] <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt
3391  || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
3392  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
3393 
3394  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3395  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
3396  lastconstraintindex - 1,
3397  "False");
3398 
3399  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3400  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
3401  lastconstraintindex,
3402  "False");
3403  }
3404  }
3405  else {
3406  std::vector<int>::const_iterator itg;
3407  std::vector<Sketcher::PointPos>::const_iterator itp;
3408 
3409  Base::Vector3d pntr = Obj->getPoint(GeoId.back(), PosId.back());
3410 
3411  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
3412  bool refpointfixed = false;
3413 
3414  if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId.back())) {
3415  refpointfixed = true;
3416  }
3417 
3418  for (itg = GeoId.begin(), itp = PosId.begin();
3419  itg != std::prev(GeoId.end()) && itp != std::prev(PosId.end());
3420  ++itp, ++itg) {
3421  bool pointfixed = false;
3422 
3423  if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, *itg)) {
3424  pointfixed = true;
3425  }
3426 
3427  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(*itg, *itp);
3428 
3429  // undo command open
3430  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add relative 'Lock' constraint"));
3431  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3432  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
3433  *itg,
3434  static_cast<int>(*itp),
3435  GeoId.back(),
3436  static_cast<int>(PosId.back()),
3437  pntr.x - pnt.x);
3438 
3439  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3440  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
3441  *itg,
3442  static_cast<int>(*itp),
3443  GeoId.back(),
3444  static_cast<int>(PosId.back()),
3445  pntr.y - pnt.y);
3446  lastconstraintindex += 2;
3447 
3448  if ((refpointfixed && pointfixed) || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
3449  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
3450 
3451  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3452  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
3453  lastconstraintindex - 1,
3454  "False");
3455 
3456  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
3457  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
3458  lastconstraintindex,
3459  "False");
3460  }
3461  }
3462  }
3463 
3464  // finish the transaction and update
3465  commitCommand();
3466  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
3467 
3468  // clear the selection (convenience)
3469  getSelection().clearSelection();
3470 }

3472 void CmdSketcherConstrainLock::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
3473 {
3474  switch (seqIndex) {
3475  case 0:// {Vertex}
3476  // Create the constraints
3477  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
3478  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
3479  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
3480 
3481  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
3482  bool pointfixed = false;
3483 
3484  if (selSeq.empty()) {
3485  return;
3486  }
3487 
3488  if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, selSeq.front().GeoId)) {
3489  pointfixed = true;
3490  }
3491 
3492  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(selSeq.front().GeoId, selSeq.front().PosId);
3493 
3494  // undo command open
3495  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add fixed constraint"));
3496  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3497  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX', %d, %d, %f))",
3498  selSeq.front().GeoId,
3499  static_cast<int>(selSeq.front().PosId),
3500  pnt.x);
3501  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3502  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY', %d, %d, %f))",
3503  selSeq.front().GeoId,
3504  static_cast<int>(selSeq.front().PosId),
3505  pnt.y);
3506 
3507  if (pointfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
3508  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
3509  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
3510 
3511  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3512  "setDriving(%d, %s)",
3513  ConStr.size() - 2,
3514  "False");
3515 
3516  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
3517  "setDriving(%d, %s)",
3518  ConStr.size() - 1,
3519  "False");
3520  }
3521 
3522  // finish the transaction and update
3523  Gui::Command::commitCommand();
3524 
3525  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
3526  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
3527  bool autoRecompute = hGrp->GetBool("AutoRecompute", false);
3528 
3529  if (autoRecompute) {
3530  Gui::Command::updateActive();
3531  }
3532  break;
3533  }
3534 }

3586 void CmdSketcherConstrainBlock::activated(int iMsg)
3587 {
3588  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
3589 
3590  // get the selection
3591  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
3592 
3593  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
3594  if (selection.size() != 1
3595  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
3596  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
3597  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
3598  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
3599 
3600  if (constraintMode) {
3601  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
3602  getSelection().clearSelection();
3603  }
3604  else {
3605  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
3606  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3607  QObject::tr("Select vertices from the sketch."));
3608  }
3609  return;
3610  }
3611 
3612  // get the needed lists and objects
3613  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
3614  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
3615 
3616  // Check that the solver does not report redundant/conflicting constraints
3617  if (Obj->getLastSolverStatus() != GCS::Success || Obj->getLastHasConflicts()
3618  || Obj->getLastHasRedundancies()) {
3619  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
3620  QObject::tr("Wrong solver status"),
3621  QObject::tr("A Block constraint cannot be added "
3622  "if the sketch is unsolved "
3623  "or there are redundant and "
3624  "conflicting constraints."));
3625  return;
3626  }
3627 
3628  std::vector<int> GeoId;
3629  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& vals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
3630 
3631  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
3632  int GeoIdt;
3633  Sketcher::PointPos PosIdt;
3634  getIdsFromName(subname, Obj, GeoIdt, PosIdt);
3635 
3636  if (isVertex(GeoIdt, PosIdt) || GeoIdt < 0) {
3637  if (selection.size() == 1) {
3638  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
3639  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3640  QObject::tr("Select one edge from the sketch."));
3641  }
3642  else {
3643  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
3644  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3645  QObject::tr("Select only edges from the sketch."));
3646  }
3647  // clear the selection
3648  getSelection().clearSelection();
3649  return;
3650  }
3651 
3652  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
3653  if (checkConstraint(vals, Sketcher::Block, GeoIdt, Sketcher::PointPos::none)) {
3654  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
3655  Obj,
3656  QObject::tr("Double constraint"),
3657  QObject::tr("The selected edge already has a Block constraint!"));
3658  return;
3659  }
3660 
3661  GeoId.push_back(GeoIdt);
3662  }
3663 
3664  for (std::vector<int>::iterator itg = GeoId.begin(); itg != GeoId.end(); ++itg) {
3665  // undo command open
3666  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add 'Block' constraint"));
3667 
3668  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
3669  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Block',%d))", (*itg));
3670  });
3671 
3672  if (!safe) {
3673  return;
3674  }
3675  else {
3676  commitCommand();
3677  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
3678  }
3679  }
3680 
3681  // clear the selection (convenience)
3682  getSelection().clearSelection();
3683 }

3802 bool CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::substituteConstraintCombinationsPointOnObject(SketchObject* Obj, int GeoId1, PointPos PosId1, int GeoId2)
3803 {
3804  const std::vector<Constraint*>& cvals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
3805 
3806  int cid = 0;
3807  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = cvals.begin(); it != cvals.end();
3808  ++it, ++cid) {
3809  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Tangent && (*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none
3810  && (*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none && (*it)->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef
3811  && (((*it)->First == GeoId1 && (*it)->Second == GeoId2)
3812  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId1 && (*it)->First == GeoId2))
3813  && (PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::start
3814  || PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
3815 
3816  // NOTE: This function does not either open or commit a command as it is used for group
3817  // addition it relies on such infrastructure being provided by the caller.
3818 
3819  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "delConstraint(%d)", cid);
3820 
3821  doEndpointToEdgeTangency(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2);
3822 
3823  notifyConstraintSubstitutions(
3824  QObject::tr("Endpoint to edge tangency was applied instead."));
3825 
3826  getSelection().clearSelection();
3827  return true;
3828  }
3829  }
3830 
3831  return false;
3832 }
3833 
3834 bool CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::substituteConstraintCombinationsCoincident(SketchObject* Obj, int GeoId1, PointPos PosId1, int GeoId2, PointPos PosId2)
3835 {
3836  // checks for direct and indirect coincidence constraints
3837  bool constraintExists = Obj->arePointsCoincident(GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2);
3838 
3839  const std::vector<Constraint*>& cvals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
3840 
3841  // NOTE: This function does not either open or commit a command as it is used for group addition
3842  // it relies on such infrastructure being provided by the caller.
3843 
3844  int j = 0;
3845  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = cvals.begin(); it != cvals.end();
3846  ++it, ++j) {
3847  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Tangent && (*it)->Third == GeoEnum::GeoUndef
3848  && (((*it)->First == GeoId1 && (*it)->Second == GeoId2)
3849  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId1 && (*it)->First == GeoId2))) {
3850  if (!(PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::start
3851  || PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
3852  || !(PosId2 == Sketcher::PointPos::start
3853  || PosId2 == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
3854  continue;
3855  }
3856  if ((*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none
3857  && (*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
3858 
3859  if (constraintExists) {
3860  // try to remove any pre-existing direct coincident constraints
3861  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
3862  "delConstraintOnPoint(%d,%d)",
3863  GeoId1,
3864  static_cast<int>(PosId1));
3865  }
3866 
3867  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "delConstraint(%d)", j);
3868 
3869  doEndpointTangency(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, PosId1, PosId2);
3870 
3871  notifyConstraintSubstitutions(
3872  QObject::tr("Endpoint to endpoint tangency was applied instead."));
3873 
3874  getSelection().clearSelection();
3875  return true;
3876  }
3877  else if (isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId1) != isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId2)) {
3878  // Replace with knot-to-endpoint tangency
3879 
3880  if (isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId2)) {
3881  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
3882  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
3883  }
3884 
3885  // if a similar tangency already exists this must result in bad constraints
3886  if ((*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
3887  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "delConstraint(%d)", j);
3888 
3889  doEndpointTangency(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, PosId1, PosId2);
3890 
3891  notifyConstraintSubstitutions(
3892  QObject::tr("B-spline knot to endpoint tangency was applied instead."));
3893 
3894  getSelection().clearSelection();
3895  return true;
3896  }
3897  }
3898  }
3899  }
3900 
3901  return false;
3902 }
3903 
3904 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::activated(int iMsg)
3905 {
3906  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
3907  onActivated(CoincicenceType::Both);
3908 }
3909 
3910 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::onActivated(CoincicenceType type)
3911 {
3912  QString errorMess;
3913  if (type == CoincicenceType::Coincident) {
3914  errorMess = QObject::tr("Select either several points, or several conics for concentricity.");
3915  }
3916  else if (type == CoincicenceType::PointOnObject) {
3917  errorMess = QObject::tr("Select either one point and several curves, or one curve and several points");
3918  }
3919  else {
3920  errorMess = QObject::tr("Select either one point and several curves or one curve and several"
3921  " points for pointOnObject, or several points for coincidence, or several conics for concentricity.");
3922  }
3923 
3924  // get the selection
3925  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
3926 
3927  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
3928  if (selection.size() != 1
3929  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
3930  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
3931  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
3932  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
3933 
3934  if (constraintMode) {
3935  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
3936  getSelection().clearSelection();
3937  }
3938  else {
3939  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(), QObject::tr("Wrong selection"), errorMess);
3940  }
3941  return;
3942  }
3943 
3944  // get the needed lists and objects
3945  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
3946  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
3947 
3948  // count curves and points
3949  std::vector<SelIdPair> points;
3950  std::vector<SelIdPair> curves;
3951  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < SubNames.size(); i++) {
3952  SelIdPair id;
3953  getIdsFromName(SubNames[i], Obj, id.GeoId, id.PosId);
3954  if (isEdge(id.GeoId, id.PosId)) {
3955  curves.push_back(id);
3956  }
3957  if (isVertex(id.GeoId, id.PosId)) {
3958  points.push_back(id);
3959  }
3960  }
3961 
3962  if (type != CoincicenceType::Coincident && ((points.size() == 1 && !curves.empty()) || (!points.empty() && curves.size() == 1))) {
3963  activatedPointOnObject(Obj, points, curves);
3964  }
3965  else if (type != CoincicenceType::PointOnObject && ((!points.empty() && curves.empty()) || (points.empty() && !curves.empty()))) {
3966  activatedCoincident(Obj, points, curves);
3967  }
3968  else {
3969  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj, QObject::tr("Wrong selection"), errorMess);
3970  }
3971 }
3972 
3973 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::activatedPointOnObject(SketchObject* obj, std::vector<SelIdPair> points, std::vector<SelIdPair> curves)
3974 {
3975  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point on object constraint"));
3976  int cnt = 0;
3977  for (std::size_t iPnt = 0; iPnt < points.size(); iPnt++) {
3978  for (std::size_t iCrv = 0; iCrv < curves.size(); iCrv++) {
3979  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(obj, points[iPnt].GeoId, curves[iCrv].GeoId)) {
3980  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(obj);
3981  continue;
3982  }
3983  if (points[iPnt].GeoId == curves[iCrv].GeoId) {
3984  continue;// constraining a point of an element onto the element is a bad idea...
3985  }
3986 
3987  const Part::Geometry* geom = obj->getGeometry(curves[iCrv].GeoId);
3988 
3989  if (geom && isBsplinePole(geom)) {
3990  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
3991  obj,
3992  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
3993  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
3994  abortCommand();
3995 
3996  continue;
3997  }
3998 
3999  if (substituteConstraintCombinationsPointOnObject(obj,
4000  points[iPnt].GeoId,
4001  points[iPnt].PosId,
4002  curves[iCrv].GeoId)) {
4003  cnt++;
4004  continue;
4005  }
4006 
4007  cnt++;
4008  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
4009  obj,
4010  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
4011  points[iPnt].GeoId,
4012  static_cast<int>(points[iPnt].PosId),
4013  curves[iCrv].GeoId);
4014  }
4015  }
4016  if (cnt) {
4017  commitCommand();
4018  getSelection().clearSelection();
4019  }
4020  else {
4021  abortCommand();
4022  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(obj,
4023  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4024  QObject::tr("None of the selected points were constrained onto the respective curves, because they are part of the same element, they are both external geometry, or the edge is not eligible."));
4025  }
4026  return;
4027 }
4028 
4029 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::activatedCoincident(SketchObject* obj, std::vector<SelIdPair> points, std::vector<SelIdPair> curves)
4030 {
4031  bool allConicsEdges = true;// If user selects only conics (circle, ellipse, arc, arcOfEllipse)
4032  // then we make concentric constraint.
4033  for (auto& curve : curves) {
4034  if (!isGeoConcentricCompatible(obj->getGeometry(curve.GeoId))) {
4035  allConicsEdges = false;
4036  }
4037 
4038  if (!allConicsEdges) {
4039  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
4040  obj,
4041  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4042  QObject::tr("Select two or more vertices from the sketch for a coincident "
4043  "constraint, or two or more circles, ellipses, arcs or arcs of ellipse "
4044  "for a concentric constraint."));
4045  return;
4046  }
4047  curve.PosId = Sketcher::PointPos::mid;
4048  }
4049 
4050  std::vector<SelIdPair> vecOfSelIdToUse = curves.empty() ? points : curves;
4051 
4052  int GeoId1 = vecOfSelIdToUse[0].GeoId;
4053  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = vecOfSelIdToUse[0].PosId;
4054 
4055  // undo command open
4056  bool constraintsAdded = false;
4057  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add coincident constraint"));
4058 
4059  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < vecOfSelIdToUse.size(); i++) {
4060  int GeoId2 = vecOfSelIdToUse[i].GeoId;
4061  Sketcher::PointPos PosId2 = vecOfSelIdToUse[i].PosId;
4062 
4063  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
4064  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
4065  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(obj);
4066  return;
4067  }
4068 
4069  // check if as a consequence of this command undesirable combinations of constraints would
4070  // arise and substitute them with more appropriate counterparts, examples:
4071  // - coincidence + tangency on edge
4072  // - point on object + tangency on edge
4073  if (substituteConstraintCombinationsCoincident(obj, GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2)) {
4074  constraintsAdded = true;
4075  break;
4076  }
4077 
4078  // check if this coincidence is already enforced (even indirectly)
4079  bool constraintExists = obj->arePointsCoincident(GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2);
4080 
4081  if (!constraintExists) {
4082  constraintsAdded = true;
4083  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(obj,
4084  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Coincident',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
4085  GeoId1,
4086  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4087  GeoId2,
4088  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
4089  }
4090  }
4091 
4092  // finish or abort the transaction and update
4093  if (constraintsAdded) {
4094  commitCommand();
4095  }
4096  else {
4097  abortCommand();
4098  }
4099 
4100  tryAutoRecompute(obj);
4101 
4102  // clear the selection (convenience)
4103  getSelection().clearSelection();
4104 }
4105 
4106 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
4107 {
4108  switch (seqIndex) {
4109  case 0:// {SelVertex, SelEdgeOrAxis}
4110  case 1:// {SelRoot, SelEdge}
4111  case 2:// {SelVertex, SelExternalEdge}
4112  case 3:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot}
4113  case 4:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertex}
4114  case 5:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertex}
4115  applyConstraintPointOnObject(selSeq, seqIndex);
4116  break;
4117  case 6:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
4118  case 7:// {SelRoot, SelVertex}
4119  case 8:// {SelEdge, SelEdge}
4120  case 9:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
4121  case 10:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
4122  seqIndex -= 6;
4123  applyConstraintCoincident(selSeq, seqIndex);
4124  break;
4125  default:
4126  return;
4127  }
4128 }
4129 
4130 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::applyConstraintPointOnObject(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
4131 {
4132  int GeoIdVt, GeoIdCrv;
4133  Sketcher::PointPos PosIdVt;
4134 
4135  switch (seqIndex) {
4136  case 0:// {SelVertex, SelEdgeOrAxis}
4137  case 1:// {SelRoot, SelEdge}
4138  case 2:// {SelVertex, SelExternalEdge}
4139  GeoIdVt = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4140  GeoIdCrv = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4141  PosIdVt = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
4142 
4143  break;
4144  case 3:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot}
4145  case 4:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertex}
4146  case 5:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertex}
4147  GeoIdVt = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4148  GeoIdCrv = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4149  PosIdVt = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
4150 
4151  break;
4152  default:
4153  return;
4154  }
4155 
4156  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
4157  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
4158  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
4159 
4160  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point on object constraint"));
4161  bool allOK = true;
4162 
4163  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoIdVt, GeoIdCrv)) {
4164  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
4165  allOK = false;
4166  }
4167  if (GeoIdVt == GeoIdCrv) {
4168  allOK = false;// constraining a point of an element onto the element is a bad idea...
4169  }
4170 
4171  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoIdCrv);
4172 
4173  if (geom && isBsplinePole(geom)) {
4174  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
4175  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4176  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
4177  abortCommand();
4178 
4179  return;
4180  }
4181 
4182  if (allOK) {
4183  if (!substituteConstraintCombinationsPointOnObject(Obj, GeoIdVt, PosIdVt, GeoIdCrv)) {
4184  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
4185  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
4186  GeoIdVt,
4187  static_cast<int>(PosIdVt),
4188  GeoIdCrv);
4189  }
4190 
4191  commitCommand();
4192  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
4193  }
4194  else {
4195  abortCommand();
4196  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
4197  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4198  QObject::tr("None of the selected points "
4199  "were constrained onto the respective curves, "
4200  "either because they are parts of the same element, "
4201  "or because they are both external geometry."));
4202  }
4203  return;
4204 }
4205 
4206 void CmdSketcherConstrainCoincidentUnified::applyConstraintCoincident(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
4207 {
4208  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
4209  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
4210  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
4211 
4212  int GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId, GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4213  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId, PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
4214 
4215  switch (seqIndex) {
4216  case 0:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
4217  case 1:// {SelRoot, SelVertex}
4218  // Nothing specific.
4219  break;
4220  case 2:// {SelEdge, SelEdge}
4221  case 3:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
4222  case 4:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
4223  // Concentric for circles, ellipse, arc, arcofEllipse only.
4224  if (!isGeoConcentricCompatible(Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1))
4225  || !isGeoConcentricCompatible(Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2))) {
4226  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
4227  Obj,
4228  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4229  QObject::tr(
4230  "Select two vertices from the sketch for a coincident constraint, or two "
4231  "circles, ellipses, arcs or arcs of ellipse for a concentric constraint."));
4232  return;
4233  }
4234  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::mid;
4235  PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::mid;
4236  break;
4237  }
4238 
4239  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
4240  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
4241  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
4242  return;
4243  }
4244 
4245  // undo command open
4246  Gui::Command::openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add coincident constraint"));
4247 
4248  // check if this coincidence is already enforced (even indirectly)
4249  bool constraintExists = Obj->arePointsCoincident(GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2);
4250  if (substituteConstraintCombinationsCoincident(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1, GeoId2, PosId2)) {}
4251  else if (!constraintExists && (GeoId1 != GeoId2)) {
4252  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
4253  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Coincident', %d, %d, %d, %d))",
4254  GeoId1,
4255  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4256  GeoId2,
4257  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
4258  }
4259  else {
4260  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
4261  return;
4262  }
4263  Gui::Command::commitCommand();
4264  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
4265 }
4266

4415 void CmdSketcherConstrainDistance::activated(int iMsg)
4416 {
4417  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
4418  // get the selection
4419  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
4420 
4421  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
4422  if (selection.size() != 1
4423  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
4424  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
4425  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
4426  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
4427 
4428  if (constraintMode) {
4429  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
4430 
4431  getSelection().clearSelection();
4432  }
4433  else {
4434  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
4435  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4436  QObject::tr("Select vertices from the sketch."));
4437  }
4438  return;
4439  }
4440 
4441  // get the needed lists and objects
4442  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
4443  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
4444 
4445  if (SubNames.empty() || SubNames.size() > 2) {
4446  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
4447  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4448  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or one point and one line "
4449  "or two points from the sketch."));
4450  return;
4451  }
4452 
4453  int GeoId1, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
4454  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
4455  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
4456  if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
4457  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
4458  }
4459 
4460  bool arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
4461 
4462  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1)
4463  && (GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis || GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis)) {
4464  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
4465  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
4466  }
4467 
4468  if ((isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) || GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis
4469  || GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis)
4470  && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// point to point distance
4471 
4472  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
4473 
4474  if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
4475  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4476 
4477  openCommand(
4478  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add distance from horizontal axis constraint"));
4479  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4480  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4481  GeoId1,
4482  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4483  GeoId2,
4484  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4485  pnt2.y);
4486  }
4487  else if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
4488  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4489 
4490  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add distance from vertical axis constraint"));
4491  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4492  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4493  GeoId1,
4494  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4495  GeoId2,
4496  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4497  pnt2.x);
4498  }
4499  else {
4500  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
4501 
4502  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to point distance constraint"));
4503  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4504  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4505  GeoId1,
4506  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4507  GeoId2,
4508  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4509  (pnt2 - pnt1).Length());
4510  }
4511 
4512  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4513  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4514  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4515 
4516  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4517  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4518  ConStr.size() - 1,
4519  "False");
4520  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4521  }
4522  else {
4523  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4524  }
4525  return;
4526  }
4527  else if ((isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2))
4528  || (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2))) {// point to line distance
4529  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
4530  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
4531  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
4532  }
4533  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
4534  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
4535 
4536  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
4537  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
4538  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = lineSeg->getStartPoint();
4539  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = lineSeg->getEndPoint();
4540  Base::Vector3d d = pnt2 - pnt1;
4541  double ActDist =
4542  std::abs(-pnt.x * d.y + pnt.y * d.x + pnt1.x * pnt2.y - pnt2.x * pnt1.y)
4543  / d.Length();
4544 
4545  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to line Distance constraint"));
4546  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4547  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4548  GeoId1,
4549  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4550  GeoId2,
4551  ActDist);
4552 
4553  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed
4554  || constraintCreationMode
4555  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4556  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4557 
4558  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4559  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4560  ConStr.size() - 1,
4561  "False");
4562  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4563  }
4564  else {
4565  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4566  }
4567 
4568  return;
4569  }
4570  else if (isCircleOrArc(*geom)) { // point to circle distance
4571  auto [radius, center] = getRadiusCenterCircleArc(geom);
4572  Base::Vector3d d = center - pnt;
4573  double ActDist = std::abs(d.Length() - radius);
4574 
4575  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to circle Distance constraint"));
4576  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4577  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4578  GeoId1,
4579  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4580  GeoId2,
4581  ActDist);
4582 
4583  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed
4584  || constraintCreationMode
4585  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4586  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4587 
4588  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4589  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4590  ConStr.size() - 1,
4591  "False");
4592  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4593  }
4594  else {
4595  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4596  }
4597 
4598  return;
4599  }
4600  }
4601  else if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
4602  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
4603  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
4604 
4605  if(isCircleOrArc(*geom1) && isCircleOrArc(*geom2)) {
4606 
4607  auto [radius1, center1] = getRadiusCenterCircleArc(geom1);
4608  auto [radius2, center2] = getRadiusCenterCircleArc(geom2);
4609 
4610  double ActDist = 0.0;
4611 
4612  Base::Vector3d intercenter = center1 - center2;
4613  double intercenterdistance = intercenter.Length();
4614 
4615  if (intercenterdistance >= radius1 && intercenterdistance >= radius2) {
4616 
4617  ActDist = intercenterdistance - radius1 - radius2;
4618  }
4619  else {
4620  double bigradius = std::max(radius1, radius2);
4621  double smallradius = std::min(radius1, radius2);
4622 
4623  ActDist = bigradius - smallradius - intercenterdistance;
4624  }
4625 
4626  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add circle to circle distance constraint"));
4627  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4628  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%f))",
4629  GeoId1,
4630  GeoId2,
4631  ActDist);
4632 
4633  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed
4634  || constraintCreationMode
4635  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4636  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4637 
4638  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4639  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4640  ConStr.size() - 1,
4641  "False");
4642  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4643  }
4644  else {
4645  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4646  }
4647 
4648  return;
4649  }
4650  else if ((isCircleOrArc(*geom1) && isLineSegment(*geom2))
4651  || (isLineSegment(*geom1) && isCircleOrArc(*geom2))) {// circle to line distance
4652 
4653  if (isLineSegment(*geom1)) {
4654  std::swap(geom1, geom2);// Assume circle is first
4655  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
4656  }
4657 
4658  auto [radius, center] = getRadiusCenterCircleArc(geom1);
4659 
4660  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom2);
4661  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = lineSeg->getStartPoint();
4662  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = lineSeg->getEndPoint();
4663  Base::Vector3d d = pnt2 - pnt1;
4664  double ActDist =
4665  std::abs(-center.x * d.y + center.y * d.x + pnt1.x * pnt2.y - pnt2.x * pnt1.y)
4666  / d.Length()
4667  - radius;
4668 
4669  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add circle to line distance constraint"));
4670  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4671  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%f)) ",
4672  GeoId1,
4673  GeoId2,
4674  ActDist);
4675 
4676  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed
4677  || constraintCreationMode
4678  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4679  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4680 
4681  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4682  "setDriving(%i,%s)",
4683  ConStr.size() - 1,
4684  "False");
4685  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4686  }
4687  else {
4688  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4689  }
4690 
4691  return;
4692  }
4693  else {
4694  Gui::TranslatedNotification(
4695  Obj,
4696  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4697  QObject::tr("Cannot add a length constraint on this selection!"));
4698  return;
4699  }
4700  }
4701  else if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)) {// line length
4702  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
4703  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
4704  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4705  QObject::tr("Cannot add a length constraint on an axis!"));
4706  return;
4707  }
4708 
4709  arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1);
4710 
4711  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
4712 
4713  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
4714  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
4715  double ActLength = (lineSeg->getEndPoint() - lineSeg->getStartPoint()).Length();
4716 
4717  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add length constraint"));
4718  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4719  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%f))",
4720  GeoId1,
4721  ActLength);
4722 
4723  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4724  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt
4725  || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4726  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4727 
4728  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4729  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4730  ConStr.size() - 1,
4731  "False");
4732  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4733  }
4734  else {
4735  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4736  }
4737 
4738  return;
4739  }
4740  else if (isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
4741  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
4742  double ActLength = arc->getAngle(false) * arc->getRadius();
4743 
4744  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add length constraint"));
4745  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4746  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%f))",
4747  GeoId1,
4748  ActLength);
4749 
4750  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4751  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt
4752  || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4753  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4754 
4755  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
4756  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
4757  ConStr.size() - 1,
4758  "False");
4759  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4760  }
4761  else {
4762  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4763  }
4764 
4765  return;
4766  }
4767  }
4768 
4769  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
4770  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4771  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or one point and one line or "
4772  "two points or two circles from the sketch."));
4773  return;
4774 }
4775 
4776 void CmdSketcherConstrainDistance::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
4777 {
4778  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
4779  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
4780  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
4781 
4782  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
4783  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
4784 
4785  bool arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
4786 
4787  switch (seqIndex) {
4788  case 0:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
4789  case 1:// {SelRoot, SelVertex}
4790  {
4791  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4792  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4793  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
4794  PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
4795 
4796  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
4797 
4798  if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
4799  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4800 
4801  openCommand(
4802  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add distance from horizontal axis constraint"));
4803  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
4804  Obj,
4805  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4806  GeoId1,
4807  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4808  GeoId2,
4809  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4810  pnt2.y);
4811  }
4812  else if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
4813  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
4814 
4815  openCommand(
4816  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add distance from vertical axis constraint"));
4817  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
4818  Obj,
4819  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4820  GeoId1,
4821  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4822  GeoId2,
4823  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4824  pnt2.x);
4825  }
4826  else {
4827  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
4828 
4829  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to point distance constraint"));
4830  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
4831  Obj,
4832  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4833  GeoId1,
4834  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4835  GeoId2,
4836  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
4837  (pnt2 - pnt1).Length());
4838  }
4839 
4840  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4841  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4842  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4843 
4844  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
4845  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4846  }
4847  else {
4848  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4849  }
4850 
4851  return;
4852  }
4853  case 2:// {SelEdge}
4854  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge}
4855  {
4856  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4857 
4858  arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1);
4859 
4860  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
4861 
4862  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
4863  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
4864  double ActLength = (lineSeg->getEndPoint() - lineSeg->getStartPoint()).Length();
4865 
4866  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add length constraint"));
4867  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
4868  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%f))",
4869  GeoId1,
4870  ActLength);
4871 
4872  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt
4873  || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4874  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4875  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4876 
4877  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
4878  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4879  }
4880  else {
4881  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4882  }
4883  }
4884  else if (isCircle(*geom)) {
4885  // allow this selection but do nothing as it needs 2 circles or 1 circle and 1 line
4886  }
4887  else {
4888  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
4889  Obj,
4890  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4891  QObject::tr("This constraint does not make sense for non-linear curves."));
4892  }
4893 
4894  return;
4895  }
4896  case 4:// {SelVertex, SelEdgeOrAxis}
4897  case 5:// {SelRoot, SelEdge}
4898  case 6:// {SelVertex, SelExternalEdge}
4899  case 7:// {SelRoot, SelExternalEdge}
4900  {
4901  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4902  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4903  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
4904 
4905  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
4906  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
4907 
4908  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
4909  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
4910  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = lineSeg->getStartPoint();
4911  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = lineSeg->getEndPoint();
4912  Base::Vector3d d = pnt2 - pnt1;
4913  double ActDist =
4914  std::abs(-pnt.x * d.y + pnt.y * d.x + pnt1.x * pnt2.y - pnt2.x * pnt1.y)
4915  / d.Length();
4916 
4917  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to line Distance constraint"));
4918  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
4919  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%d,%f))",
4920  GeoId1,
4921  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
4922  GeoId2,
4923  ActDist);
4924 
4925  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
4926  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4927  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4928 
4929  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
4930  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4931  }
4932  else {
4933  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4934  }
4935  }
4936 
4937  return;
4938  }
4939  case 8:// {SelEdge, SelEdge}
4940  {
4941  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
4942  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
4943  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
4944  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
4945 
4946  if (isCircle(*geom1) && isCircle(*geom2)) {// circle to circle distance
4947  auto circleSeg1 = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom1);
4948  double radius1 = circleSeg1->getRadius();
4949  Base::Vector3d center1 = circleSeg1->getCenter();
4950 
4951  auto circleSeg2 = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom2);
4952  double radius2 = circleSeg2->getRadius();
4953  Base::Vector3d center2 = circleSeg2->getCenter();
4954 
4955  double ActDist = 0.;
4956 
4957  Base::Vector3d intercenter = center1 - center2;
4958  double intercenterdistance = intercenter.Length();
4959 
4960  if (intercenterdistance >= radius1 && intercenterdistance >= radius2) {
4961 
4962  ActDist = intercenterdistance - radius1 - radius2;
4963  }
4964  else {
4965  double bigradius = std::max(radius1, radius2);
4966  double smallradius = std::min(radius1, radius2);
4967 
4968  ActDist = bigradius - smallradius - intercenterdistance;
4969  }
4970 
4971  openCommand(
4972  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add circle to circle distance constraint"));
4973  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
4974  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Distance',%d,%d,%f))",
4975  GeoId1,
4976  GeoId2,
4977  ActDist);
4978 
4979  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed
4980  || constraintCreationMode
4981  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
4982  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
4983 
4984  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
4985  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
4986  }
4987  else {
4988  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
4989  }
4990 
4991  return;
4992  }
4993  else {
4994  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
4995  Obj,
4996  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
4997  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or one point and one line or two points "
4998  "or two circles from the sketch."));
4999  }
5000  }
5001  default:
5002  break;
5003  }
5004 }

5063 void CmdSketcherConstrainDistanceX::activated(int iMsg)
5064 {
5065  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
5066  // get the selection
5067  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
5068 
5069  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
5070  if (selection.size() != 1
5071  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
5072  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
5073  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
5074  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
5075 
5076  if (constraintMode) {
5077  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
5078  getSelection().clearSelection();
5079  }
5080  else {
5081  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
5082  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
5083  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5084  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
5085  }
5086  return;
5087  }
5088 
5089  // get the needed lists and objects
5090  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
5091  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
5092 
5093  if (SubNames.empty() || SubNames.size() > 2) {
5094  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5095  Obj,
5096  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5097  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or up to two points from the sketch."));
5098  return;
5099  }
5100 
5101  int GeoId1, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5102  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5103  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
5104  if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
5105  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
5106  }
5107 
5108  bool arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
5109 
5110  if (GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis || GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5111  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5112  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5113  }
5114 
5115  if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5116  // reject horizontal axis from selection
5117  GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5118  }
5119  else if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5120  GeoId1 = Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis;
5121  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5122  }
5123 
5124  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && GeoId2 == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5125  // horizontal length of a line
5126  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5127  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5128  Obj,
5129  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5130  QObject::tr("Cannot add a horizontal length constraint on an axis!"));
5131  return;
5132  }
5133 
5134  arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1);
5135 
5136  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
5137 
5138  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
5139  // convert to as if two endpoints of the line have been selected
5140  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5141  GeoId2 = GeoId1;
5142  PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
5143  }
5144  }
5145  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
5146  // point to point horizontal distance
5147  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
5148  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
5149  double ActLength = pnt2.x - pnt1.x;
5150 
5151  // negative sign avoidance: swap the points to make value positive
5152  if (ActLength < -Precision::Confusion()) {
5153  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5154  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5155  std::swap(pnt1, pnt2);
5156  ActLength = -ActLength;
5157  }
5158 
5159  openCommand(
5160  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to point horizontal distance constraint"));
5161  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5162  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
5163  GeoId1,
5164  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
5165  GeoId2,
5166  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
5167  ActLength);
5168 
5169  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
5170  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
5171  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
5172 
5173  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5174  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
5175  ConStr.size() - 1,
5176  "False");
5177  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
5178  }
5179  else {
5180  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
5181  }
5182 
5183  return;
5184  }
5185  else if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && GeoId2 == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5186  // point on fixed x-coordinate
5187 
5188  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5189  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5190  Obj,
5191  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5192  QObject::tr("Cannot add a fixed x-coordinate constraint on the origin point!"));
5193  return;
5194  }
5195 
5196  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
5197  double ActX = pnt.x;
5198 
5199  arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1);
5200 
5201  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add fixed x-coordinate constraint"));
5202  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5203  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%f))",
5204  GeoId1,
5205  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
5206  ActX);
5207 
5208  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
5209  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
5210  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
5211 
5212  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5213  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
5214  ConStr.size() - 1,
5215  "False");
5216  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
5217  }
5218  else {
5219  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
5220  }
5221 
5222  return;
5223  }
5224 
5225  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5226  Obj,
5227  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5228  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or up to two points from the sketch."));
5229  return;
5230 }
5231 
5232 void CmdSketcherConstrainDistanceX::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
5233 {
5234  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
5235  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
5236  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
5237 
5238  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5239  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5240 
5241  switch (seqIndex) {
5242  case 0:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
5243  case 1:// {SelRoot, SelVertex}
5244  {
5245  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
5246  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
5247  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
5248  PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
5249  break;
5250  }
5251  case 2:// {SelEdge}
5252  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge}
5253  {
5254  GeoId1 = GeoId2 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
5255  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5256  PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
5257 
5258  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
5259 
5260  if (! isLineSegment(*geom)) {
5261  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5262  Obj,
5263  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5264  QObject::tr(
5265  "This constraint only makes sense on a line segment or a pair of points."));
5266  return;
5267  }
5268 
5269  break;
5270  }
5271  default:
5272  break;
5273  }
5274 
5275  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
5276  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
5277  double ActLength = pnt2.x - pnt1.x;
5278 
5279  // negative sign avoidance: swap the points to make value positive
5280  if (ActLength < -Precision::Confusion()) {
5281  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5282  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5283  std::swap(pnt1, pnt2);
5284  ActLength = -ActLength;
5285  }
5286 
5287  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to point horizontal distance constraint"));
5288  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
5289  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceX',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
5290  GeoId1,
5291  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
5292  GeoId2,
5293  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
5294  ActLength);
5295 
5296  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2) || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
5297  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
5298  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
5299 
5300  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
5301  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
5302  }
5303  else {
5304  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
5305  }
5306 }

5312  if (getAction()) {
5313  getAction()->setIcon(
5314  Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_HorizontalDistance_Driven"));
5315  }
5316  break;
5317  case Driving:
5318  if (getAction()) {
5319  getAction()->setIcon(
5320  Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_HorizontalDistance"));
5321  }
5322  break;
5323  }
5324 }
