5366 void CmdSketcherConstrainDistanceY::activated(int iMsg)
5367 {
5368  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
5369  // get the selection
5370  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
5371 
5372  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
5373  if (selection.size() != 1
5374  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
5375  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
5376  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
5377  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
5378 
5379  if (constraintMode) {
5380  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
5381  getSelection().clearSelection();
5382  }
5383  else {
5384  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
5385  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
5386  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5387  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
5388  }
5389  return;
5390  }
5391 
5392  // get the needed lists and objects
5393  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
5394  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
5395 
5396  if (SubNames.empty() || SubNames.size() > 2) {
5397  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5398  Obj,
5399  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5400  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or up to two points from the sketch."));
5401  return;
5402  }
5403 
5404  int GeoId1, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5405  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
5406  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
5407  if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
5408  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
5409  }
5410 
5411  bool arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
5412 
5413  if (GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis || GeoId2 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5414  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5415  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5416  }
5417 
5418  if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis
5419  && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {// reject vertical axis from selection
5420  GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
5421  }
5422  else if (GeoId1 == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis && PosId1 == Sketcher::PointPos::none) {
5423  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5424  }
5425 
5426  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && GeoId2 == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {// vertical length of a line
5427  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5428  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5429  Obj,
5430  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5431  QObject::tr("Cannot add a vertical length constraint on an axis!"));
5432  return;
5433  }
5434 
5435  arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId1);
5436 
5437  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
5438 
5439  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
5440  // convert to as if two endpoints of the line have been selected
5441  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
5442  GeoId2 = GeoId1;
5443  PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
5444  }
5445  }
5446 
5447  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
5448  // point to point vertical distance
5449  Base::Vector3d pnt1 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
5450  Base::Vector3d pnt2 = Obj->getPoint(GeoId2, PosId2);
5451  double ActLength = pnt2.y - pnt1.y;
5452 
5453  // negative sign avoidance: swap the points to make value positive
5454  if (ActLength < -Precision::Confusion()) {
5455  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5456  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5457  std::swap(pnt1, pnt2);
5458  ActLength = -ActLength;
5459  }
5460 
5461  openCommand(
5462  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add point to point vertical distance constraint"));
5463  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5464  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
5465  GeoId1,
5466  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
5467  GeoId2,
5468  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
5469  ActLength);
5470 
5471  if (arebothpointsorsegmentsfixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
5472  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
5473  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
5474 
5475  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5476  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
5477  ConStr.size() - 1,
5478  "False");
5479  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
5480  }
5481  else {
5482  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
5483  }
5484 
5485  return;
5486  }
5487  else if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && GeoId2 == GeoEnum::GeoUndef) {
5488  // point on fixed y-coordinate
5489  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
5490  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5491  Obj,
5492  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5493  QObject::tr("Cannot add a fixed y-coordinate constraint on the origin point!"));
5494  return;
5495  }
5496 
5497  Base::Vector3d pnt = Obj->getPoint(GeoId1, PosId1);
5498  double ActY = pnt.y;
5499 
5500  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add fixed y-coordinate constraint"));
5501  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5502  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('DistanceY',%d,%d,%f))",
5503  GeoId1,
5504  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
5505  ActY);
5506 
5507  if (GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
5508  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
5509  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
5510 
5511  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5512  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
5513  ConStr.size() - 1,
5514  "False");
5515  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
5516  }
5517  else {
5518  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
5519  }
5520 
5521  return;
5522  }
5523 
5524  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5525  Obj,
5526  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5527  QObject::tr("Select exactly one line or up to two points from the sketch."));
5528  return;
5529 }

5664 void CmdSketcherConstrainParallel::activated(int iMsg)
5665 {
5666  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
5667  // get the selection
5668  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
5669 
5670  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
5671  if (selection.size() != 1
5672  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
5673  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
5674  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
5675  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
5676 
5677  if (constraintMode) {
5678  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
5679  getSelection().clearSelection();
5680  }
5681  else {
5682  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
5683  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
5684  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5685  QObject::tr("Select two or more lines from the sketch."));
5686  }
5687  return;
5688  }
5689 
5690  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
5691 
5692  // go through the selected subelements
5693  std::vector<int> ids;
5694  bool hasAlreadyExternal = false;
5695  for (auto& subname : selection[0].getSubNames()) {
5696 
5697  int GeoId;
5698  Sketcher::PointPos PosId;
5699  getIdsFromName(subname, Obj, GeoId, PosId);
5700 
5701  if (!isEdge(GeoId, PosId)) {
5702  continue;
5703  }
5704  else if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId)) {
5705  if (hasAlreadyExternal) {
5706  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
5707  return;
5708  }
5709  else {
5710  hasAlreadyExternal = true;
5711  }
5712  }
5713 
5714  // Check that the curve is a line segment
5715  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
5716 
5717  if (!isLineSegment(*geo)) {
5718  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
5719  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5720  QObject::tr("One selected edge is not a valid line."));
5721  return;
5722  }
5723  ids.push_back(GeoId);
5724  }
5725 
5726  if (ids.size() < 2) {
5727  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
5728  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5729  QObject::tr("Select at least two lines from the sketch."));
5730  return;
5731  }
5732 
5733  // undo command open
5734  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add parallel constraint"));
5735  for (int i = 0; i < int(ids.size() - 1); i++) {
5736  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
5737  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Parallel',%d,%d))",
5738  ids[i],
5739  ids[i + 1]);
5740  }
5741  // finish the transaction and update
5742  commitCommand();
5743 
5744  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
5745 
5746  // clear the selection (convenience)
5747  getSelection().clearSelection();
5748 }
5749 
5750 void CmdSketcherConstrainParallel::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
5751 {
5752  switch (seqIndex) {
5753  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
5754  case 1:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
5755  case 2:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
5756  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
5757  // create the constraint
5758  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
5759  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
5760  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
5761 
5762  int GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId, GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
5763 
5764  // Check that the curves are line segments
5765  if (! isLineSegment(*(Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1))) || ! isLineSegment(*(Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2)))) {
5766  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
5767  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5768  QObject::tr("The selected edge is not a valid line."));
5769  return;
5770  }
5771 
5772  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
5773  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
5774  return;
5775  }
5776 
5777  // undo command open
5778  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add parallel constraint"));
5779  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(sketchgui->getObject(),
5780  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Parallel',%d,%d))",
5781  GeoId1,
5782  GeoId2);
5783  // finish the transaction and update
5784  commitCommand();
5785  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
5786  }
5787 }

5807 CmdSketcherConstrainPerpendicular::CmdSketcherConstrainPerpendicular()

5824  {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge},
5825  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis},
5826  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge},
5827  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelExternalEdge},
5828  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelEdge},
5829  {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis},
5830  {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge},
5831  {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge},
5832  {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}};
5833  ;
5834 }
5835 
5836 void CmdSketcherConstrainPerpendicular::activated(int iMsg)
5837 {
5838  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
5839 
5840  // get the selection
5841  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
5842 
5843  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
5844  if (selection.size() != 1
5845  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
5846  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
5847  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
5848  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
5849 
5850  if (constraintMode) {
5851  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
5852  getSelection().clearSelection();
5853  }
5854  else {
5855  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
5856  QString strBasicHelp =
5857  QObject::tr("There is a number of ways this constraint can be applied.\n\n"
5858  "Accepted combinations: two curves; an endpoint and a curve; two "
5859  "endpoints; two curves and a point.",
5860  /*disambig.:*/ "perpendicular constraint");
5861  QString strError =
5862  QObject::tr("Select some geometry from the sketch.", "perpendicular constraint");
5863  strError.append(QString::fromLatin1("\n\n"));
5864  strError.append(strBasicHelp);
5865  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
5866  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5867  std::move(strError));
5868  }
5869  return;
5870  }
5871 
5872  // get the needed lists and objects
5873  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
5874  auto* Obj = dynamic_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
5875 
5876  if (!Obj || (SubNames.size() != 2 && SubNames.size() != 3)) {
5877  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
5878  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5879  QObject::tr("Wrong number of selected objects!"));
5880  return;
5881  }
5882 
5883  int GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3;
5884  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2, PosId3;
5885  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
5886  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
5887 
5888  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj,
5889  GeoId1,
5890  GeoId2)) {// checkBothExternal displays error message
5891  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
5892  return;
5893  }
5894 
5895  if (SubNames.size() == 3) {// perpendicular via point
5896  getIdsFromName(SubNames[2], Obj, GeoId3, PosId3);
5897  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3. We want to keep the order the two curves have been
5898  // selected in.
5899  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1)) {
5900  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
5901  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
5902  }
5903  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
5904  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
5905  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
5906  }
5907 
5908  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
5909 
5910  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
5911  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5912  Obj,
5913  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5914  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
5915  return;
5916  }
5917 
5918  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
5919 
5920  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
5921  // add missing point-on-object constraints
5922  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
5923  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
5924  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
5925  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
5926  selection[0].getObject(),
5927  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
5928  GeoId3,
5929  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
5930  GeoId1);
5931  }
5932  }
5933 
5934  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
5935  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
5936  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
5937  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
5938  selection[0].getObject(),
5939  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
5940  GeoId3,
5941  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
5942  GeoId2);
5943  }
5944  }
5945 
5946  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(
5947  GeoId1,
5948  GeoId3,
5949  PosId3,
5950  Obj)) {
5951  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
5952  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
5953  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
5954  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
5955  selection[0].getObject(),
5956  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
5957  GeoId3,
5958  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
5959  GeoId1);
5960  }
5961  }
5962 
5963  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
5964  selection[0].getObject(),
5965  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PerpendicularViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
5966  GeoId1,
5967  GeoId2,
5968  GeoId3,
5969  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
5970 
5971  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
5972  });
5973 
5974  if (!safe) {
5975  return;
5976  }
5977  else {
5978  commitCommand();
5979  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
5980  }
5981 
5982  getSelection().clearSelection();
5983 
5984  return;
5985  }
5986 
5987  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5988  Obj,
5989  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
5990  QObject::tr("With 3 objects, there must be 2 curves and 1 point."));
5991  }
5992  else if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
5993  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1)
5994  && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// endpoint-to-endpoint perpendicularity
5995 
5996  if (isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1) || isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId2, PosId2)) {
5997  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
5998  Obj,
5999  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6000  QObject::tr(
6001  "Cannot add a perpendicularity constraint at an unconnected point!"));
6002  return;
6003  }
6004 
6005  // This code supports simple B-spline endpoint perp to any other geometric curve
6006  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6007  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6008 
6009  if (geom1 && geom2 && (isBSplineCurve(*geom1) || isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
6010  if (! isBSplineCurve(*geom1)) {
6011  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6012  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
6013  }
6014  // GeoId1 is the B-spline now
6015  }// end of code supports simple B-spline endpoint tangency
6016 
6017  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6018  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
6019  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Perpendicular',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
6020  GeoId1,
6021  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
6022  GeoId2,
6023  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
6024  commitCommand();
6025  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6026 
6027  getSelection().clearSelection();
6028  return;
6029  }
6030  else if ((isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2))
6031  || (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2))) {// endpoint-to-curve
6032  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
6033  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6034  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
6035  }
6036 
6037  if (isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1)) {
6038  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6039  Obj,
6040  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6041  QObject::tr(
6042  "Cannot add a perpendicularity constraint at an unconnected point!"));
6043  return;
6044  }
6045 
6046  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6047 
6048  if (isBsplinePole(geom2)) {
6049  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6050  Obj,
6051  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6052  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6053  return;
6054  }
6055 
6056  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicularity constraint"));
6057  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
6058  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Perpendicular',%d,%d,%d))",
6059  GeoId1,
6060  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
6061  GeoId2);
6062  commitCommand();
6063  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6064 
6065  getSelection().clearSelection();
6066  return;
6067  }
6068  else if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)
6069  && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// simple perpendicularity between GeoId1 and GeoId2
6070 
6071  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6072  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6073  if (!geo1 || !geo2) {
6074  return;
6075  }
6076 
6077  if (! isLineSegment(*geo1) && ! isLineSegment(*geo2)) {
6078  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6079  Obj,
6080  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6081  QObject::tr("One of the selected edges should be a line."));
6082  return;
6083  }
6084 
6085  // if (isBSplineCurve(*geo1) || isBSplineCurve(*geo2)) {
6086  // // unsupported until tangent to B-spline at any point implemented.
6087  // Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6088  // Obj,
6089  // QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6090  // QObject::tr("Perpendicular to B-spline edge currently unsupported."));
6091  // return;
6092  // }
6093 
6094  if (isLineSegment(*geo1)) {
6095  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6096  }
6097 
6098  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1)) {
6099  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6100  Obj,
6101  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6102  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6103  return;
6104  }
6105 
6106  // GeoId2 is the line
6107  geo1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6108  geo2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6109 
6110  if (isEllipse(*geo1) || isArcOfEllipse(*geo1) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1) || isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6111  Base::Vector3d center;
6112  Base::Vector3d majdir;
6113  Base::Vector3d focus;
6114  double majord = 0;
6115  double minord = 0;
6116  double phi = 0;
6117 
6118  if (isEllipse(*geo1)) {
6119  auto ellipse = static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geo1);
6120  center = ellipse->getCenter();
6121  majord = ellipse->getMajorRadius();
6122  minord = ellipse->getMinorRadius();
6123  majdir = ellipse->getMajorAxisDir();
6124  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6125  }
6126  else if (isArcOfEllipse(*geo1)) {
6127  auto aoe = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geo1);
6128  center = aoe->getCenter();
6129  majord = aoe->getMajorRadius();
6130  minord = aoe->getMinorRadius();
6131  majdir = aoe->getMajorAxisDir();
6132  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6133  }
6134  else if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1)) {
6135  auto aoh = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geo1);
6136  center = aoh->getCenter();
6137  majord = aoh->getMajorRadius();
6138  minord = aoh->getMinorRadius();
6139  majdir = aoh->getMajorAxisDir();
6140  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6141  }
6142  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6143  auto aop = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geo1);
6144  center = aop->getCenter();
6145  focus = aop->getFocus();
6146  }
6147 
6148  const Part::GeomLineSegment* line = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo2);
6149 
6150  Base::Vector3d point1 = line->getStartPoint();
6151  Base::Vector3d PoO;
6152 
6153  if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1)) {
6154  double df = sqrt(majord * majord + minord * minord);
6155  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - (center + majdir * df);// towards the focus
6156  double tapprox = atan2(direction.y, direction.x) - phi;
6157 
6158  PoO = Base::Vector3d(center.x + majord * cosh(tapprox) * cos(phi)
6159  - minord * sinh(tapprox) * sin(phi),
6160  center.y + majord * cosh(tapprox) * sin(phi)
6161  + minord * sinh(tapprox) * cos(phi),
6162  0);
6163  }
6164  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6165  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - focus;// towards the focus
6166 
6167  PoO = point1 + direction / 2;
6168  }
6169  else {
6170  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - center;
6171  double tapprox = atan2(direction.y, direction.x)
6172  - phi;// we approximate the eccentric anomaly by the polar
6173 
6174  PoO = Base::Vector3d(center.x + majord * cos(tapprox) * cos(phi)
6175  - minord * sin(tapprox) * sin(phi),
6176  center.y + majord * cos(tapprox) * sin(phi)
6177  + minord * sin(tapprox) * cos(phi),
6178  0);
6179  }
6180  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6181 
6182  try {
6183  // Add a point
6184  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
6185  "addGeometry(Part.Point(App.Vector(%f,%f,0)), True)",
6186  PoO.x,
6187  PoO.y);
6188  int GeoIdPoint = Obj->getHighestCurveIndex();
6189 
6190  // Point on first object (ellipse, arc of ellipse)
6191  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6192  selection[0].getObject(),
6193  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6194  GeoIdPoint,
6195  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start),
6196  GeoId1);
6197  // Point on second object
6198  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6199  selection[0].getObject(),
6200  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6201  GeoIdPoint,
6202  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start),
6203  GeoId2);
6204  // add constraint: Perpendicular-via-point
6205  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6206  Obj,
6207  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PerpendicularViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
6208  GeoId1,
6209  GeoId2,
6210  GeoIdPoint,
6211  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start));
6212  }
6213  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
6214  Gui::NotifyUserError(Obj,
6215  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications", "Invalid Constraint"),
6216  e.what());
6217  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
6218 
6219  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6220  return;
6221  }
6222 
6223  commitCommand();
6224  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6225 
6226  getSelection().clearSelection();
6227  return;
6228  }
6229 
6230  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6231  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
6232  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Perpendicular',%d,%d))",
6233  GeoId1,
6234  GeoId2);
6235  commitCommand();
6236  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6237 
6238  getSelection().clearSelection();
6239  return;
6240  }
6241  }
6242 
6243  return;
6244 }
6245 
6246 void CmdSketcherConstrainPerpendicular::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq,
6247  int seqIndex)
6248 {
6249  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
6250  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
6251  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
6252 
6253  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId3 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
6254  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none,
6255  PosId3 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
6256 
6257  switch (seqIndex) {
6258  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
6259  case 1:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
6260  case 2:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
6261  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
6262  {
6263  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
6264  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
6265 
6266  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
6267  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
6268  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
6269  return;
6270  }
6271 
6272  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6273  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6274  if (!geo1 || !geo2) {
6275  return;
6276  }
6277 
6278  if (! isLineSegment(*geo1) && ! isLineSegment(*geo2)) {
6279  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6280  Obj,
6281  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6282  QObject::tr("One of the selected edges should be a line."));
6283  return;
6284  }
6285 
6286  // if (isBSplineCurve(*geo1) || isBSplineCurve(*geo2)) {
6287  // // unsupported until tangent to B-spline at any point implemented.
6288  // Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6289  // Obj,
6290  // QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6291  // QObject::tr("Perpendicular to B-spline edge currently unsupported."));
6292  // return;
6293  // }
6294 
6295  if (isLineSegment(*geo1)) {
6296  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6297  }
6298 
6299  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1)) {
6300  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6301  Obj,
6302  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6303  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6304  return;
6305  }
6306 
6307  // GeoId2 is the line
6308  geo1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6309  geo2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6310 
6311  if (isEllipse(*geo1) || isArcOfEllipse(*geo1) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1) || isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6312  Base::Vector3d center;
6313  Base::Vector3d majdir;
6314  Base::Vector3d focus;
6315  double majord = 0;
6316  double minord = 0;
6317  double phi = 0;
6318 
6319  if (isEllipse(*geo1)) {
6320  auto ellipse = static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geo1);
6321  center = ellipse->getCenter();
6322  majord = ellipse->getMajorRadius();
6323  minord = ellipse->getMinorRadius();
6324  majdir = ellipse->getMajorAxisDir();
6325  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6326  }
6327  else if (isArcOfEllipse(*geo1)) {
6328  auto aoe = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geo1);
6329  center = aoe->getCenter();
6330  majord = aoe->getMajorRadius();
6331  minord = aoe->getMinorRadius();
6332  majdir = aoe->getMajorAxisDir();
6333  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6334  }
6335  else if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1)) {
6336  auto aoh = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geo1);
6337  center = aoh->getCenter();
6338  majord = aoh->getMajorRadius();
6339  minord = aoh->getMinorRadius();
6340  majdir = aoh->getMajorAxisDir();
6341  phi = atan2(majdir.y, majdir.x);
6342  }
6343  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6344  auto aop = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geo1);
6345  center = aop->getCenter();
6346  focus = aop->getFocus();
6347  }
6348 
6349  const Part::GeomLineSegment* line = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geo2);
6350 
6351  Base::Vector3d point1 = line->getStartPoint();
6352  Base::Vector3d PoO;
6353 
6354  if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1)) {
6355  double df = sqrt(majord * majord + minord * minord);
6356  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - (center + majdir * df);// towards the focus
6357  double tapprox = atan2(direction.y, direction.x) - phi;
6358 
6359  PoO = Base::Vector3d(center.x + majord * cosh(tapprox) * cos(phi)
6360  - minord * sinh(tapprox) * sin(phi),
6361  center.y + majord * cosh(tapprox) * sin(phi)
6362  + minord * sinh(tapprox) * cos(phi),
6363  0);
6364  }
6365  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geo1)) {
6366  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - focus;// towards the focus
6367 
6368  PoO = point1 + direction / 2;
6369  }
6370  else {
6371  Base::Vector3d direction = point1 - center;
6372  double tapprox = atan2(direction.y, direction.x)
6373  - phi;// we approximate the eccentric anomaly by the polar
6374 
6375  PoO = Base::Vector3d(center.x + majord * cos(tapprox) * cos(phi)
6376  - minord * sin(tapprox) * sin(phi),
6377  center.y + majord * cos(tapprox) * sin(phi)
6378  + minord * sin(tapprox) * cos(phi),
6379  0);
6380  }
6381  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6382 
6383  try {
6384  // Add a point
6385  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
6386  "addGeometry(Part.Point(App.Vector(%f,%f,0)), True)",
6387  PoO.x,
6388  PoO.y);
6389  int GeoIdPoint = Obj->getHighestCurveIndex();
6390 
6391  // Point on first object (ellipse, arc of ellipse)
6392  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6393  Obj,
6394  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6395  GeoIdPoint,
6396  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start),
6397  GeoId1);
6398  // Point on second object
6399  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6400  Obj,
6401  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6402  GeoIdPoint,
6403  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start),
6404  GeoId2);
6405 
6406  // add constraint: Perpendicular-via-point
6407  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6408  Obj,
6409  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PerpendicularViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
6410  GeoId1,
6411  GeoId2,
6412  GeoIdPoint,
6413  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start));
6414 
6415  commitCommand();
6416  }
6417  catch (const Base::Exception& e) {
6418  Gui::NotifyUserError(Obj,
6419  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Notifications", "Invalid Constraint"),
6420  e.what());
6421  Gui::Command::abortCommand();
6422  }
6423 
6424  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6425 
6426  getSelection().clearSelection();
6427  return;
6428  }
6429 
6430  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6431  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
6432  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Perpendicular',%d,%d))",
6433  GeoId1,
6434  GeoId2);
6435  commitCommand();
6436 
6437  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6438  return;
6439  }
6440  case 4:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
6441  case 5:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
6442  case 6:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
6443  case 7:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
6444  {
6445  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3.
6446  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
6447  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
6448  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
6449  PosId3 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
6450 
6451  break;
6452  }
6453  case 8: // {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis}
6454  case 9: // {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
6455  case 10:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge}
6456  case 11:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
6457  {
6458  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3.
6459  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
6460  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
6461  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
6462  PosId3 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
6463 
6464  break;
6465  }
6466  default:
6467  return;
6468  }
6469 
6470  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
6471 
6472  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
6473  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
6474  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
6475  return;
6476  }
6477 
6478  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
6479  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6480  Obj,
6481  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6482  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6483  return;
6484  }
6485 
6486  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add perpendicular constraint"));
6487 
6488  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
6489  // add missing point-on-object constraints
6490  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6491  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6492  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
6493  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6494  Obj,
6495  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6496  GeoId3,
6497  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6498  GeoId1);
6499  }
6500  }
6501 
6502  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6503  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6504  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
6505  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6506  Obj,
6507  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6508  GeoId3,
6509  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6510  GeoId2);
6511  }
6512  }
6513 
6514  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6515  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
6516  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6517  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
6518  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6519  Obj,
6520  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6521  GeoId3,
6522  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6523  GeoId1);
6524  }
6525  }
6526 
6527  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6528  Obj,
6529  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PerpendicularViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
6530  GeoId1,
6531  GeoId2,
6532  GeoId3,
6533  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
6534 
6535  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
6536  });
6537 
6538  if (!safe) {
6539  return;
6540  }
6541  else {
6542  commitCommand();
6543  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6544  }
6545 
6546  getSelection().clearSelection();
6547 
6548  return;
6549  }
6550 }
6551 
6552 // ======================================================================================

6554 class CmdSketcherConstrainTangent: public CmdSketcherConstraint
6555 {
6556 public:
6557  CmdSketcherConstrainTangent();
6558  ~CmdSketcherConstrainTangent() override
6559  {}
6560  const char* className() const override
6561  {
6562  return "CmdSketcherConstrainTangent";
6563  }
6564 
6565 protected:
6566  void activated(int iMsg) override;
6567  void applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex) override;
6568  // returns true if a substitution took place
6569  static bool substituteConstraintCombinations(SketchObject* Obj, int GeoId1, int GeoId2);
6570 };

6572 CmdSketcherConstrainTangent::CmdSketcherConstrainTangent()
6573  : CmdSketcherConstraint("Sketcher_ConstrainTangent")
6574 {
6575  sAppModule = "Sketcher";
6576  sGroup = "Sketcher";
6577  sMenuText = QT_TR_NOOP("Constrain tangent or collinear");
6578  sToolTipText = QT_TR_NOOP("Create a tangent or collinear constraint between two entities");
6579  sWhatsThis = "Sketcher_ConstrainTangent";
6580  sStatusTip = sToolTipText;
6581  sPixmap = "Constraint_Tangent";
6582  sAccel = "T";
6583  eType = ForEdit;
6584 
6585  allowedSelSequences = {
6586  {SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis},
6587  {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge},
6588  {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge},
6589  {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}, /* Two Curves */
6590  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis},
6591  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge},
6592  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelExternalEdge},
6593  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelEdge},
6594  {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis},
6595  {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge},
6596  {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge},
6597  {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}, /* Two Curves and a Point */
6598  {SelVertexOrRoot, SelVertex} /*Two Endpoints*/ /*No Place for One Endpoint and One Curve*/};
6599 }
6600 
6601 bool CmdSketcherConstrainTangent::substituteConstraintCombinations(SketchObject* Obj,
6602  int GeoId1,
6603  int GeoId2)
6604 {
6605  const std::vector<Constraint*>& cvals = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
6606 
6607  int cid = 0;
6608  for (std::vector<Constraint*>::const_iterator it = cvals.begin(); it != cvals.end();
6609  ++it, ++cid) {
6610  if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::Coincident
6611  && (((*it)->First == GeoId1 && (*it)->Second == GeoId2)
6612  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId1 && (*it)->First == GeoId2))
6613  && ((*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start
6614  || (*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)
6615  && ((*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start
6616  || (*it)->SecondPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
6617  // save values because 'doEndpointTangency' changes the
6618  // constraint property and thus invalidates this iterator
6619  int first = (*it)->First;
6620  int firstpos = static_cast<int>((*it)->FirstPos);
6621 
6622  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6623  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Swap coincident+tangency with ptp tangency"));
6624 
6625  doEndpointTangency(Obj, (*it)->First, (*it)->Second, (*it)->FirstPos, (*it)->SecondPos);
6626 
6627  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "delConstraintOnPoint(%d,%d)", first, firstpos);
6628 
6629  commitCommand();
6630  Obj->solve();// The substitution requires a solve() so that the autoremove redundants
6631  // works when Autorecompute not active.
6632  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(Obj);
6633 
6634  notifyConstraintSubstitutions(QObject::tr("Endpoint to endpoint tangency was applied. "
6635  "The coincident constraint was deleted."));
6636 
6637  getSelection().clearSelection();
6638  return true;
6639  }
6640  else if ((*it)->Type == Sketcher::PointOnObject
6641  && (((*it)->First == GeoId1 && (*it)->Second == GeoId2)
6642  || ((*it)->Second == GeoId1 && (*it)->First == GeoId2))
6643  && ((*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::start
6644  || (*it)->FirstPos == Sketcher::PointPos::end)) {
6645  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6646  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command",
6647  "Swap point on object and tangency with point to curve tangency"));
6648 
6649  doEndpointToEdgeTangency(Obj, (*it)->First, (*it)->FirstPos, (*it)->Second);
6650 
6651  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
6652  "delConstraint(%d)",
6653  cid);// remove the preexisting point on object constraint.
6654 
6655  commitCommand();
6656 
6657  // A substitution requires a solve() so that the autoremove redundants works when
6658  // Autorecompute not active. However, delConstraint includes such solve() internally. So
6659  // at this point it is already solved.
6660  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(Obj);
6661 
6662  notifyConstraintSubstitutions(QObject::tr("Endpoint to edge tangency was applied. The "
6663  "point on object constraint was deleted."));
6664 
6665  getSelection().clearSelection();
6666  return true;
6667  }
6668  }
6669 
6670  return false;
6671 }
6672 
6673 void CmdSketcherConstrainTangent::activated(int iMsg)
6674 {
6675  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
6676 
6677  // get the selection
6678  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
6679 
6680  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
6681  if (selection.size() != 1
6682  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
6683  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
6684  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
6685  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
6686 
6687  if (constraintMode) {
6688  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
6689  getSelection().clearSelection();
6690  }
6691  else {
6692  QString strBasicHelp =
6693  QObject::tr("There are a number of ways this constraint can be applied.\n\n"
6694  "Accepted combinations: two curves; an endpoint and a curve; two "
6695  "endpoints; two curves and a point.",
6696  /*disambig.:*/ "tangent constraint");
6697  QString strError =
6698  QObject::tr("Select some geometry from the sketch.", "tangent constraint");
6699  strError.append(QString::fromLatin1("\n\n"));
6700  strError.append(strBasicHelp);
6701  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
6702  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6703  std::move(strError));
6704  }
6705  return;
6706  }
6707 
6708  // get the needed lists and objects
6709  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
6710  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
6711 
6712  if (SubNames.size() != 2 && SubNames.size() != 3) {
6713  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
6714  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6715  QObject::tr("Wrong number of selected objects!"));
6716  return;
6717  }
6718 
6719  int GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3;
6720  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2, PosId3;
6721  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
6722  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
6723 
6724  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj,
6725  GeoId1,
6726  GeoId2)) {// checkBothExternal displays error message
6727  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
6728  return;
6729  }
6730  if (SubNames.size() == 3) {// tangent via point
6731  getIdsFromName(SubNames[2], Obj, GeoId3, PosId3);
6732  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3. We want to keep the order the two curves have been
6733  // selected in.
6734  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1)) {
6735  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6736  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
6737  }
6738  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
6739  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
6740  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
6741  }
6742 
6743  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
6744 
6745  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
6746  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6747  Obj,
6748  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6749  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6750  return;
6751  }
6752 
6753  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
6754 
6755  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
6756  // add missing point-on-object constraints
6757  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6758  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6759  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
6760  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6761  selection[0].getObject(),
6762  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6763  GeoId3,
6764  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6765  GeoId1);
6766  }
6767  }
6768 
6769  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6770  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6771  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
6772  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6773  selection[0].getObject(),
6774  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6775  GeoId3,
6776  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6777  GeoId2);
6778  }
6779  }
6780 
6781  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
6782  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
6783  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6784  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
6785  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6786  selection[0].getObject(),
6787  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
6788  GeoId3,
6789  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
6790  GeoId1);
6791  }
6792  }
6793 
6794  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
6795  selection[0].getObject(),
6796  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('TangentViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
6797  GeoId1,
6798  GeoId2,
6799  GeoId3,
6800  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
6801 
6802  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
6803  });
6804 
6805  if (!safe) {
6806  return;
6807  }
6808  else {
6809  commitCommand();
6810  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6811  }
6812 
6813  getSelection().clearSelection();
6814 
6815  return;
6816  }
6817 
6818  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6819  Obj,
6820  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6821  QObject::tr("With 3 objects, there must be 2 curves and 1 point."));
6822  }
6823  else if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
6824 
6825  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// endpoint-to-endpoint tangency
6826 
6827  if (isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId2)) {
6828  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6829  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
6830  }
6831 
6832  if (isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1) || isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId2, PosId2)) {
6833 
6834  if (isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId1)) {
6835  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6836 
6837  if (! geom2 || ! isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
6838  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6839  Obj,
6840  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6841  QObject::tr("Tangent constraint at B-spline knot is only supported "
6842  "with lines!"));
6843  return;
6844  }
6845  }
6846  else {
6847  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6848  Obj,
6849  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6850  QObject::tr("Cannot add a tangency constraint at an unconnected point!"));
6851  return;
6852  }
6853  }
6854 
6855  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
6856  doEndpointTangency(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, PosId1, PosId2);
6857  commitCommand();
6858  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6859 
6860  getSelection().clearSelection();
6861  return;
6862  }
6863  else if ((isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2))
6864  || (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)
6865  && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2))) {// endpoint-to-curve/knot-to-curve tangency
6866  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
6867  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6868  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
6869  }
6870 
6871  if (isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1)) {
6872  if (isBsplineKnot(Obj, GeoId1)) {
6873  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6874 
6875  if (!geom2 || ! isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
6876  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6877  Obj,
6878  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6879  QObject::tr("Tangent constraint at B-spline knot is only supported "
6880  "with lines!"));
6881  return;
6882  }
6883  }
6884  else {
6885  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6886  Obj,
6887  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6888  QObject::tr("Cannot add a tangency constraint at an unconnected point!"));
6889  return;
6890  }
6891  }
6892 
6893  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6894 
6895  if (isBsplinePole(geom2)) {
6896  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6897  Obj,
6898  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6899  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6900  return;
6901  }
6902 
6903  if (!substituteConstraintCombinations(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
6904  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
6905  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
6906  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Tangent',%d,%d,%d))",
6907  GeoId1,
6908  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
6909  GeoId2);
6910  commitCommand();
6911  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
6912 
6913  getSelection().clearSelection();
6914  }
6915  return;
6916  }
6917  else if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)
6918  && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// simple tangency between GeoId1 and GeoId2
6919 
6920  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6921  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6922 
6923  if (isBsplinePole(geom1) || isBsplinePole(geom2)) {
6924  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
6925  Obj,
6926  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
6927  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
6928  return;
6929  }
6930 
6931  // check if as a consequence of this command undesirable combinations of constraints
6932  // would arise and substitute them with more appropriate counterparts, examples:
6933  // - coincidence + tangency on edge
6934  // - point on object + tangency on edge
6935  if (substituteConstraintCombinations(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
6936  return;
6937  }
6938 
6939  if (geom1 && geom2 && (isEllipse(*geom1) || isEllipse(*geom2))) {
6940  if (! isEllipse(*geom1)) {
6941  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6942  }
6943 
6944  // GeoId1 is the ellipse
6945  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6946  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6947 
6948  if (isEllipse(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2) || isCircle(*geom2) || isArcOfCircle(*geom2)) {
6949  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6950  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
6951  makeTangentToEllipseviaNewPoint(Obj,
6952  static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geom1),
6953  geom2,
6954  GeoId1,
6955  GeoId2);
6956  getSelection().clearSelection();
6957  return;
6958  }
6959  else if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2)) {
6960  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6961  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
6962  makeTangentToArcOfHyperbolaviaNewPoint(
6963  Obj,
6964  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geom2),
6965  geom1,
6966  GeoId2,
6967  GeoId1);
6968  getSelection().clearSelection();
6969  return;
6970  }
6971  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2)) {
6972  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6973  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
6974  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
6975  Obj,
6976  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom2),
6977  geom1,
6978  GeoId2,
6979  GeoId1);
6980  getSelection().clearSelection();
6981  return;
6982  }
6983  }
6984  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isArcOfEllipse(*geom1) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2))) {
6985  if (! isArcOfEllipse(*geom1)) {
6986  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
6987  }
6988 
6989  // GeoId1 is the arc of ellipse
6990  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
6991  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
6992 
6993  if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2)
6994  || isCircle(*geom2) || isArcOfCircle(*geom2) || isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
6995 
6996  Gui::Command::openCommand(
6997  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
6998  makeTangentToArcOfEllipseviaNewPoint(
6999  Obj,
7000  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfEllipse*>(geom1),
7001  geom2,
7002  GeoId1,
7003  GeoId2);
7004 
7005  getSelection().clearSelection();
7006  return;
7007  }
7008  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2)) {
7009  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7010  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7011  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7012  Obj,
7013  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom2),
7014  geom1,
7015  GeoId2,
7016  GeoId1);
7017  getSelection().clearSelection();
7018  return;
7019  }
7020  }
7021  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom1) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2))) {
7022  if (! isArcOfHyperbola(*geom1)) {
7023  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7024  }
7025 
7026  // GeoId1 is the arc of hyperbola
7027  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7028  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7029 
7030  if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2) || isCircle(*geom2)
7031  || isArcOfCircle(*geom2) || isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
7032 
7033  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7034  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7035  makeTangentToArcOfHyperbolaviaNewPoint(
7036  Obj,
7037  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geom1),
7038  geom2,
7039  GeoId1,
7040  GeoId2);
7041  getSelection().clearSelection();
7042  return;
7043  }
7044  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2)) {
7045  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7046  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7047  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7048  Obj,
7049  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom2),
7050  geom1,
7051  GeoId2,
7052  GeoId1);
7053  getSelection().clearSelection();
7054  return;
7055  }
7056  }
7057  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isArcOfParabola(*geom1) || isArcOfParabola(*geom2))) {
7058  if (! isArcOfParabola(*geom1)) {
7059  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7060  }
7061 
7062  // GeoId1 is the arc of hyperbola
7063  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7064  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7065 
7066  if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2)
7067  || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2) || isCircle(*geom2)
7068  || isArcOfCircle(*geom2) || isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
7069 
7070  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7071  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7072  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7073  Obj,
7074  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom1),
7075  geom2,
7076  GeoId1,
7077  GeoId2);
7078  getSelection().clearSelection();
7079  return;
7080  }
7081  }
7082  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isBSplineCurve(*geom1) || isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
7083  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7084  Obj,
7085  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7086  QObject::tr("Only tangent-via-point is supported with a B-spline."));
7087  getSelection().clearSelection();
7088  return;
7089  }
7090 
7091  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
7092  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7093  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Tangent',%d,%d))",
7094  GeoId1,
7095  GeoId2);
7096  commitCommand();
7097  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
7098 
7099  getSelection().clearSelection();
7100  return;
7101  }
7102  }
7103 
7104  return;
7105 }
7106 
7107 void CmdSketcherConstrainTangent::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
7108 {
7109  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
7110  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
7111  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
7112 
7113  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId3 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
7114  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none,
7115  PosId3 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
7116 
7117  switch (seqIndex) {
7118  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
7119  case 1:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
7120  case 2:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
7121  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
7122  {
7123  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
7124  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
7125 
7126  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
7127  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
7128  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
7129  return;
7130  }
7131 
7132  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7133  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7134 
7135  if (isBsplinePole(geom1) || isBsplinePole(geom2)) {
7136  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7137  Obj,
7138  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7139  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
7140  return;
7141  }
7142 
7143  // check if as a consequence of this command undesirable combinations of constraints
7144  // would arise and substitute them with more appropriate counterparts, examples:
7145  // - coincidence + tangency on edge
7146  // - point on object + tangency on edge
7147  if (substituteConstraintCombinations(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
7148  return;
7149  }
7150 
7151  if (geom1 && geom2 && (isEllipse(*geom1) || isEllipse(*geom2))) {
7152  if (! isEllipse(*geom1)) {
7153  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7154  }
7155 
7156  // GeoId1 is the ellipse
7157  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7158  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7159 
7160  if (isEllipse(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2)
7161  || isCircle(*geom2) || isArcOfCircle(*geom2)) {
7162 
7163  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7164  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7165  makeTangentToEllipseviaNewPoint(Obj,
7166  static_cast<const Part::GeomEllipse*>(geom1),
7167  geom2,
7168  GeoId1,
7169  GeoId2);
7170  getSelection().clearSelection();
7171  return;
7172  }
7173  else if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2)) {
7174  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7175  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7176  makeTangentToArcOfHyperbolaviaNewPoint(
7177  Obj,
7178  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geom2),
7179  geom1,
7180  GeoId2,
7181  GeoId1);
7182  getSelection().clearSelection();
7183  return;
7184  }
7185  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2)) {
7186  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7187  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7188  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7189  Obj,
7190  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom2),
7191  geom1,
7192  GeoId2,
7193  GeoId1);
7194  getSelection().clearSelection();
7195  return;
7196  }
7197  }
7198  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom1) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2))) {
7199  if (! isArcOfHyperbola(*geom1)) {
7200  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7201  }
7202 
7203  // GeoId1 is the arc of hyperbola
7204  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7205  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7206 
7207  if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2) || isCircle(*geom2)
7208  || isArcOfCircle(*geom2) || isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
7209 
7210  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7211  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7212  makeTangentToArcOfHyperbolaviaNewPoint(
7213  Obj,
7214  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfHyperbola*>(geom1),
7215  geom2,
7216  GeoId1,
7217  GeoId2);
7218  getSelection().clearSelection();
7219  return;
7220  }
7221  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2)) {
7222  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7223  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7224  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7225  Obj,
7226  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom2),
7227  geom1,
7228  GeoId2,
7229  GeoId1);
7230  getSelection().clearSelection();
7231  return;
7232  }
7233  }
7234  else if (geom1 && geom2 && (isArcOfParabola(*geom1) || isArcOfParabola(*geom2))) {
7235  if (! isArcOfParabola(*geom1)) {
7236  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7237  }
7238 
7239  // GeoId1 is the arc of hyperbola
7240  geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7241  geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7242 
7243  if (isArcOfParabola(*geom2) || isArcOfHyperbola(*geom2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geom2)
7244  || isCircle(*geom2) || isArcOfCircle(*geom2) || isLineSegment(*geom2)) {
7245 
7246  Gui::Command::openCommand(
7247  QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint point"));
7248  makeTangentToArcOfParabolaviaNewPoint(
7249  Obj,
7250  static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfParabola*>(geom1),
7251  geom2,
7252  GeoId1,
7253  GeoId2);
7254  getSelection().clearSelection();
7255  return;
7256  }
7257  }
7258 
7259  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
7260  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7261  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Tangent',%d,%d))",
7262  GeoId1,
7263  GeoId2);
7264  commitCommand();
7265  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
7266 
7267  return;
7268  }
7269  case 4:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
7270  case 5:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
7271  case 6:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
7272  case 7:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
7273  {
7274  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3.
7275  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
7276  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
7277  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
7278  PosId3 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
7279 
7280  break;
7281  }
7282  case 8: // {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis}
7283  case 9: // {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
7284  case 10:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge}
7285  case 11:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
7286  {
7287  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3.
7288  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
7289  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
7290  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
7291  PosId3 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
7292 
7293  break;
7294  }
7295  case 12:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelVertex}
7296  {
7297  // Different notation than the previous places
7298  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
7299  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
7300  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
7301  PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
7302 
7303  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
7304  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
7305  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
7306  return;
7307  }
7308 
7309  if (isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1) || isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId2, PosId2)) {
7310  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7311  Obj,
7312  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7313  QObject::tr("Cannot add a tangency constraint at an unconnected point!"));
7314  return;
7315  }
7316 
7317  // This code supports simple B-spline endpoint tangency to any other geometric curve
7318  const Part::Geometry* geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7319  const Part::Geometry* geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7320 
7321  if (geom1 && geom2 && (isBSplineCurve(*geom1) || isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
7322  if (! isBSplineCurve(*geom1)) {
7323  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
7324  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
7325  }
7326  // GeoId1 is the B-spline now
7327  }// end of code supports simple B-spline endpoint tangency
7328 
7329  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
7330  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7331  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Tangent',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
7332  GeoId1,
7333  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
7334  GeoId2,
7335  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
7336  commitCommand();
7337  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
7338 
7339  getSelection().clearSelection();
7340  return;
7341  }
7342  default:
7343  return;
7344  }
7345 
7346  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
7347 
7348  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
7349  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
7350  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
7351  return;
7352  }
7353 
7354  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
7355  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7356  Obj,
7357  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7358  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
7359  return;
7360  }
7361 
7362  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add tangent constraint"));
7363 
7364  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
7365  // add missing point-on-object constraints
7366  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
7367  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7368  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
7369  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
7370  Obj,
7371  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
7372  GeoId3,
7373  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
7374  GeoId1);
7375  }
7376  }
7377 
7378  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
7379  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
7380  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
7381  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
7382  Obj,
7383  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
7384  GeoId3,
7385  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
7386  GeoId2);
7387  }
7388  }
7389 
7390  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
7391  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
7392  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
7393  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
7394  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
7395  Obj,
7396  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
7397  GeoId3,
7398  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
7399  GeoId1);
7400  }
7401  }
7402 
7403  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
7404  Obj,
7405  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('TangentViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
7406  GeoId1,
7407  GeoId2,
7408  GeoId3,
7409  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
7410 
7411  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
7412  });
7413 
7414  if (!safe) {
7415  return;
7416  }
7417  else {
7418  commitCommand();
7419  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
7420  }
7421 
7422  getSelection().clearSelection();
7423 
7424  return;
7425  }
7426 }

7462 
7463 void CmdSketcherConstrainRadius::activated(int iMsg)
7464 {
7465  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
7466  // get the selection
7467  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
7468 
7469  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
7470  if (selection.size() != 1
7471  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
7472  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
7473  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
7474  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
7475 
7476  if (constraintMode) {
7477  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
7478  getSelection().clearSelection();
7479  }
7480  else {
7481  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
7482  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
7483  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7484  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
7485  }
7486  return;
7487  }
7488 
7489  // get the needed lists and objects
7490  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
7491  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
7492 
7493  if (SubNames.empty()) {
7494  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7495  Obj,
7496  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7497  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
7498  return;
7499  }
7500 
7501  // check for which selected geometry the constraint can be applied
7502  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> geoIdRadiusMap;
7503  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> externalGeoIdRadiusMap;
7504 
7505  bool poles = false;
7506  bool nonpoles = false;
7507 
7508  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
7509  bool issegmentfixed = false;
7510  int GeoId;
7511 
7512  if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 4) == "Edge") {
7513  GeoId = std::atoi(subname.substr(4, 4000).c_str()) - 1;
7514  issegmentfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId);
7515  }
7516  else if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 12) == "ExternalEdge") {
7517  GeoId = -std::atoi(subname.substr(12, 4000).c_str()) - 2;
7518  issegmentfixed = true;
7519  }
7520  else {
7521  continue;
7522  }
7523 
7524  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
7525 
7526  if (geom && isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
7527  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
7528  double radius = arc->getRadius();
7529 
7530  if (issegmentfixed) {
7531  externalGeoIdRadiusMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
7532  }
7533  else {
7534  geoIdRadiusMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
7535  }
7536 
7537  nonpoles = true;
7538  }
7539  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
7540  auto circle = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
7541  double radius = circle->getRadius();
7542 
7543  if (issegmentfixed) {
7544  externalGeoIdRadiusMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
7545  }
7546  else {
7547  geoIdRadiusMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
7548  }
7549 
7550  if (isBsplinePole(geom)) {
7551  poles = true;
7552  }
7553  else {
7554  nonpoles = true;
7555  }
7556  }
7557  }
7558 
7559  if (geoIdRadiusMap.empty() && externalGeoIdRadiusMap.empty()) {
7560  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7561  Obj,
7562  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7563  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
7564  return;
7565  }
7566 
7567  if (poles && nonpoles) {
7568  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7569  Obj,
7570  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7571  QObject::tr("Select either only one or more B-spline poles or only one or more arcs or "
7572  "circles from the sketch, but not mixed."));
7573  return;
7574  }
7575 
7576  bool commitNeeded = false;
7577  bool updateNeeded = false;
7578  bool commandopened = false;
7579 
7580  if (!externalGeoIdRadiusMap.empty()) {
7581  // Create the non-driving radius constraints now
7582  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radius constraint"));
7583  commandopened = true;
7584  unsigned int constrSize = 0;
7585 
7586  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = externalGeoIdRadiusMap.begin();
7587  it != externalGeoIdRadiusMap.end();
7588  ++it) {
7589 
7590  if (nonpoles) {
7591  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7592  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
7593  it->first,
7594  it->second);
7595  }
7596  else {
7597  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7598  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
7599  it->first,
7600  it->second);
7601  }
7602 
7603  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
7604 
7605  constrSize = ConStr.size();
7606 
7607  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7608  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
7609  constrSize - 1,
7610  "False");
7611  }
7612 
7613  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false, externalGeoIdRadiusMap.size());
7614 
7615  commitNeeded = true;
7616  updateNeeded = true;
7617  }
7618 
7619  if (!geoIdRadiusMap.empty()) {
7620  if (geoIdRadiusMap.size() > 1 && constraintCreationMode == Driving) {
7621 
7622  int refGeoId = geoIdRadiusMap.front().first;
7623  double radius = geoIdRadiusMap.front().second;
7624 
7625  if (!commandopened) {
7626  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radius constraint"));
7627  }
7628 
7629  // Add the equality constraints
7630  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdRadiusMap.begin() + 1;
7631  it != geoIdRadiusMap.end();
7632  ++it) {
7633  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7634  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Equal',%d,%d))",
7635  refGeoId,
7636  it->first);
7637  }
7638 
7639  if (nonpoles) {
7640  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7641  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
7642  refGeoId,
7643  radius);
7644  }
7645  else {
7646  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7647  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
7648  refGeoId,
7649  radius);
7650  }
7651  }
7652  else {
7653  // Create the radius constraints now
7654  if (!commandopened) {
7655  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radius constraint"));
7656  }
7657  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdRadiusMap.begin();
7658  it != geoIdRadiusMap.end();
7659  ++it) {
7660  if (nonpoles) {
7661  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7662  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
7663  it->first,
7664  it->second);
7665  }
7666  else {
7667  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7668  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
7669  it->first,
7670  it->second);
7671  }
7672 
7673  if (constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
7674  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
7675  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
7676  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
7677  ConStr.size() - 1,
7678  "False");
7679  }
7680  }
7681  }
7682 
7683  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, constraintCreationMode == Driving);
7684 
7685  // updateActive();
7686  getSelection().clearSelection();
7687  }
7688 
7689  if (commitNeeded) {
7690  commitCommand();
7691  }
7692 
7693  if (updateNeeded) {
7694  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(Obj);// we have to update the solver after this aborted addition.
7695  }
7696 }
7697 
7698 void CmdSketcherConstrainRadius::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
7699 {
7700  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
7701  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
7702  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
7703 
7704  int GeoId = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
7705  double radius = 0.0;
7706 
7707  bool updateNeeded = false;
7708 
7709  switch (seqIndex) {
7710  case 0:// {SelEdge}
7711  case 1:// {SelExternalEdge}
7712  {
7713  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
7714 
7715  if (geom && isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
7716  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
7717  radius = arc->getRadius();
7718  }
7719  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
7720  auto circle = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
7721  radius = circle->getRadius();
7722  }
7723  else {
7724  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7725  Obj,
7726  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7727  QObject::tr("Constraint only applies to arcs or circles."));
7728  return;
7729  }
7730 
7731  // Create the radius constraint now
7732  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radius constraint"));
7733 
7734  bool ispole = isBsplinePole(geom);
7735 
7736  if (ispole) {
7737  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7738  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
7739  GeoId,
7740  radius);
7741  }
7742  else {
7743  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7744  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
7745  GeoId,
7746  radius);
7747  }
7748 
7749  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
7750 
7751  bool fixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId);
7752  if (fixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
7753  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
7754 
7755  updateNeeded = true;// We do need to update the solver DoF after setting the
7756  // constraint driving.
7757  }
7758 
7759  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, constraintCreationMode == Driving && !fixed);
7760 
7761  // updateActive();
7762  getSelection().clearSelection();
7763 
7764  commitCommand();
7765 
7766  if (updateNeeded) {
7767  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(
7768  Obj);// we have to update the solver after this aborted addition.
7769  }
7770  }
7771  }
7772 }
7773 
7774 void CmdSketcherConstrainRadius::updateAction(int mode)
7775 {
7776  switch (mode) {
7777  case Reference:
7778  if (getAction()) {
7779  getAction()->setIcon(
7780  Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_Radius_Driven"));
7781  }
7782  break;
7783  case Driving:
7784  if (getAction()) {
7785  getAction()->setIcon(Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_Radius"));
7786  }
7787  break;
7788  }
7789 }

7826 void CmdSketcherConstrainDiameter::activated(int iMsg)
7827 {
7828  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
7829  // get the selection
7830  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
7831 
7832  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
7833  if (selection.size() != 1
7834  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
7835  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
7836  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
7837  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
7838 
7839  if (constraintMode) {
7840  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
7841  getSelection().clearSelection();
7842  }
7843  else {
7844  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
7845  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
7846  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7847  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
7848  }
7849  return;
7850  }
7851 
7852  // get the needed lists and objects
7853  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
7854  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
7855 
7856  if (SubNames.empty()) {
7857  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7858  Obj,
7859  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7860  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
7861  return;
7862  }
7863 
7864  // check for which selected geometry the constraint can be applied
7865  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> geoIdDiameterMap;
7866  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> externalGeoIdDiameterMap;
7867 
7868  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
7869  bool issegmentfixed = false;
7870  int GeoId;
7871 
7872  if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 4) == "Edge") {
7873  GeoId = std::atoi(subname.substr(4, 4000).c_str()) - 1;
7874  issegmentfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId);
7875  }
7876  else if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 12) == "ExternalEdge") {
7877  GeoId = -std::atoi(subname.substr(12, 4000).c_str()) - 2;
7878  issegmentfixed = true;
7879  }
7880  else {
7881  continue;
7882  }
7883 
7884  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
7885 
7886  if (geom && isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
7887  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
7888  double radius = arc->getRadius();
7889 
7890  if (issegmentfixed) {
7891  externalGeoIdDiameterMap.emplace_back(GeoId, 2 * radius);
7892  }
7893  else {
7894  geoIdDiameterMap.emplace_back(GeoId, 2 * radius);
7895  }
7896  }
7897  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
7898  auto circle = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
7899  double radius = circle->getRadius();
7900 
7901  if (isBsplinePole(geom)) {
7902  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7903  Obj,
7904  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7905  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
7906 
7907  continue;
7908  }
7909 
7910  if (issegmentfixed) {
7911  externalGeoIdDiameterMap.emplace_back(GeoId, 2 * radius);
7912  }
7913  else {
7914  geoIdDiameterMap.emplace_back(GeoId, 2 * radius);
7915  }
7916  }
7917  }
7918 
7919  if (geoIdDiameterMap.empty() && externalGeoIdDiameterMap.empty()) {
7920  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
7921  Obj,
7922  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
7923  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
7924  return;
7925  }
7926 
7927  bool commitNeeded = false;
7928  bool updateNeeded = false;
7929  bool commandopened = false;
7930 
7931  if (!externalGeoIdDiameterMap.empty()) {
7932  // Create the non-driving radius constraints now
7933  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add diameter constraint"));
7934  commandopened = true;
7935  unsigned int constrSize = 0;
7936 
7937  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = externalGeoIdDiameterMap.begin();
7938  it != externalGeoIdDiameterMap.end();
7939  ++it) {
7940  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7941  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
7942  it->first,
7943  it->second);
7944 
7945  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
7946 
7947  constrSize = ConStr.size();
7948 
7949  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", constrSize - 1, "False");
7950  }
7951 
7952  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false, externalGeoIdDiameterMap.size());
7953 
7954  commitNeeded = true;
7955  updateNeeded = true;
7956  }
7957 
7958  if (!geoIdDiameterMap.empty()) {
7959  if (geoIdDiameterMap.size() > 1 && constraintCreationMode == Driving) {
7960 
7961  int refGeoId = geoIdDiameterMap.front().first;
7962  double diameter = geoIdDiameterMap.front().second;
7963 
7964  if (!commandopened) {
7965  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add diameter constraint"));
7966  }
7967 
7968  // Add the equality constraints
7969  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdDiameterMap.begin() + 1;
7970  it != geoIdDiameterMap.end();
7971  ++it) {
7972  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7973  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Equal',%d,%d))",
7974  refGeoId,
7975  it->first);
7976  }
7977 
7978  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7979  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
7980  refGeoId,
7981  diameter);
7982  }
7983  else {
7984  // Create the diameter constraints now
7985  if (!commandopened) {
7986  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add diameter constraint"));
7987  }
7988  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdDiameterMap.begin();
7989  it != geoIdDiameterMap.end();
7990  ++it) {
7991  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
7992  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
7993  it->first,
7994  it->second);
7995 
7996  if (constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
7997 
7998  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
7999 
8000  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
8001  }
8002  }
8003  }
8004 
8005  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, constraintCreationMode == Driving);
8006 
8007  // updateActive();
8008  getSelection().clearSelection();
8009  }
8010 
8011  if (commitNeeded) {
8012  commitCommand();
8013  }
8014 
8015  if (updateNeeded) {
8016  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(Obj);// we have to update the solver after this aborted addition.
8017  }
8018 }
