8020 void CmdSketcherConstrainDiameter::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
8021 {
8022  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
8023  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
8024  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();

8032  case 0:// {SelEdge}
8033  case 1:// {SelExternalEdge}

8038  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
8039  diameter = 2 * arc->getRadius();
8040  }
8041  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
8042  auto circle = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
8043  diameter = 2 * circle->getRadius();
8044  }
8045  else {
8046  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8047  Obj,

8058  return;
8059  }

8062  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add diameter constraint"));

8064  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
8065  GeoId,
8066  diameter);

8073  updateNeeded = true;// We do need to update the solver DoF after setting the
8074  // constraint driving.
8075  }
8076

8079  // updateActive();
8080  getSelection().clearSelection();
8081 
8082  commitCommand();
8083 
8084  if (updateNeeded) {

8157 
8158  if (constraintMode) {

8160  getSelection().clearSelection();
8161  }
8162  else {
8163  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
8164  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
8165  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8166  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
8167  }
8168  return;
8169  }
8170 
8171  // get the needed lists and objects
8172  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
8173  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
8174 
8175  if (SubNames.empty()) {
8176  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8177  Obj,
8178  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8179  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
8180  return;
8181  }
8182 
8183  // check for which selected geometry the constraint can be applied
8184  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> geoIdRadiamMap;
8185  std::vector<std::pair<int, double>> externalGeoIdRadiamMap;
8186 
8187  bool poles = false;
8188  bool nonpoles = false;
8189 
8190  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
8191  bool issegmentfixed = false;
8192  int GeoId;
8193 
8194  if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 4) == "Edge") {
8195  GeoId = std::atoi(subname.substr(4, 4000).c_str()) - 1;
8196  issegmentfixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId);
8197  }
8198  else if (subname.size() > 4 && subname.substr(0, 12) == "ExternalEdge") {
8199  GeoId = -std::atoi(subname.substr(12, 4000).c_str()) - 2;
8200  issegmentfixed = true;
8201  }
8202  else {
8203  continue;
8204  }
8205 
8206  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
8207  double radius;
8208 
8209  if (geom && isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
8210  auto arcir = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
8211  radius = arcir->getRadius();
8212  nonpoles = true;
8213  }
8214  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
8215  auto arcir = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
8216  radius = arcir->getRadius();
8217  if (isBsplinePole(geom)) {
8218  poles = true;
8219  }
8220  else {
8221  nonpoles = true;
8222  }
8223  }
8224  else {
8225  continue;
8226  }
8227 
8228  if (issegmentfixed) {
8229  externalGeoIdRadiamMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
8230  }
8231  else {
8232  geoIdRadiamMap.emplace_back(GeoId, radius);
8233  }
8234  }
8235 
8236  if (geoIdRadiamMap.empty() && externalGeoIdRadiamMap.empty()) {
8237  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8238  Obj,
8239  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8240  QObject::tr("Select one or more arcs or circles from the sketch."));
8241  return;
8242  }
8243 
8244  if (poles && nonpoles) {
8245  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8246  Obj,
8247  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8248  QObject::tr("Select either only one or more B-spline poles or only one or more arcs or "
8249  "circles from the sketch, but not mixed."));
8250  return;
8251  }
8252 
8253  bool commitNeeded = false;
8254  bool updateNeeded = false;
8255  bool commandopened = false;
8256 
8257  if (!externalGeoIdRadiamMap.empty()) {
8258  // Create the non-driving radiam constraints now
8259  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radiam constraint"));
8260  commandopened = true;
8261  unsigned int constrSize = 0;
8262 
8263  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = externalGeoIdRadiamMap.begin();
8264  it != externalGeoIdRadiamMap.end();
8265  ++it) {
8266  if (isArcOfCircle(*(Obj->getGeometry(it->first)))) {
8267  if (nonpoles) {
8268  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8269  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
8270  it->first,
8271  it->second);
8272  }
8273  else {
8274  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8275  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
8276  it->first,
8277  it->second);
8278  }
8279  }
8280  else {
8281  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8282  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
8283  it->first,
8284  it->second * 2);
8285  }
8286 
8287  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8288 
8289  constrSize = ConStr.size();
8290 
8291  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", constrSize - 1, "False");
8292  }
8293 
8294  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false, externalGeoIdRadiamMap.size());
8295 
8296  commitNeeded = true;
8297  updateNeeded = true;
8298  }
8299 
8300  if (!geoIdRadiamMap.empty()) {
8301  if (geoIdRadiamMap.size() > 1 && constraintCreationMode == Driving) {
8302 
8303  int refGeoId = geoIdRadiamMap.front().first;
8304  double radiam = geoIdRadiamMap.front().second;
8305 
8306  if (!commandopened) {
8307  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radiam constraint"));
8308  }
8309 
8310  // Add the equality constraints
8311  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdRadiamMap.begin() + 1;
8312  it != geoIdRadiamMap.end();
8313  ++it) {
8314  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8315  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Equal',%d,%d))",
8316  refGeoId,
8317  it->first);
8318  }
8319 
8320  if (poles) {
8321  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8322  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
8323  refGeoId,
8324  radiam);
8325  }
8326  else if (isCircle(*(Obj->getGeometry(refGeoId)))) {
8327  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8328  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
8329  refGeoId,
8330  radiam * 2);
8331  }
8332  else {
8333  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8334  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
8335  refGeoId,
8336  radiam);
8337  }
8338  }
8339  else {
8340  // Create the radiam constraints now
8341  if (!commandopened) {
8342  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radiam constraint"));
8343  }
8344  for (std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>::iterator it = geoIdRadiamMap.begin();
8345  it != geoIdRadiamMap.end();
8346  ++it) {
8347  if (poles) {
8348  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8349  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
8350  it->first,
8351  it->second);
8352  }
8353  else if (isCircle(*(Obj->getGeometry(it->first)))){
8354  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8355  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
8356  it->first,
8357  it->second * 2);
8358  }
8359  else {
8360  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8361  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
8362  it->first,
8363  it->second);
8364  }
8365 
8366  if (constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
8367 
8368  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8369 
8370  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
8371  }
8372  }
8373  }
8374 
8375  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, constraintCreationMode == Driving);
8376 
8377  // updateActive();
8378  getSelection().clearSelection();
8379  }
8380 
8381  if (commitNeeded) {
8382  commitCommand();
8383  }
8384 
8385  if (updateNeeded) {
8386  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(Obj);// we have to update the solver after this aborted addition.
8387  }
8388 }
8389 
8390 void CmdSketcherConstrainRadiam::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
8391 {
8392  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
8393  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
8394  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
8395 
8396  int GeoId = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
8397  double radiam = 0.0;
8398 
8399  bool updateNeeded = false;
8400 
8401  bool isCircleGeom = false;
8402  bool isPole = false;
8403 
8404  switch (seqIndex) {
8405  case 0:// {SelEdge}
8406  case 1:// {SelExternalEdge}
8407  {
8408  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
8409 
8410  if (geom && isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
8411  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
8412  radiam = arc->getRadius();
8413  }
8414  else if (geom && isCircle(*geom)) {
8415  auto circle = static_cast<const Part::GeomCircle*>(geom);
8416  radiam = circle->getRadius();
8417  isCircleGeom= true;
8418  if (isBsplinePole(geom)) {
8419  isPole = true;
8420  }
8421  }
8422  else {
8423  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8424  Obj,
8425  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8426  QObject::tr("Constraint only applies to arcs or circles."));
8427  return;
8428  }
8429 
8430  // Create the radiam constraint now
8431  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add radiam constraint"));
8432 
8433  if (isPole) {
8434  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8435  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Weight',%d,%f))",
8436  GeoId,
8437  radiam);
8438  }
8439  else if (isCircleGeom) {
8440  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8441  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Diameter',%d,%f))",
8442  GeoId,
8443  radiam * 2);
8444  }
8445  else {
8446  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
8447  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Radius',%d,%f))",
8448  GeoId,
8449  radiam);
8450  }
8451 
8452  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8453 
8454  bool fixed = isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId);
8455  if (fixed || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
8456  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
8457  updateNeeded = true;// We do need to update the solver DoF after setting the
8458  // constraint driving.
8459  }
8460 
8461  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, constraintCreationMode == Driving && !fixed);
8462 
8463  // updateActive();
8464  getSelection().clearSelection();
8465 
8466  commitCommand();
8467 
8468  if (updateNeeded) {
8469  tryAutoRecomputeIfNotSolve(
8470  Obj);// we have to update the solver after this aborted addition.
8471  }
8472  }
8473  }
8474 }

8479  case Reference:
8480  if (getAction()) {
8481  getAction()->setIcon(
8482  Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_Radiam_Driven"));
8483  }
8484  break;
8485  case Driving:
8486  if (getAction()) {
8487  getAction()->setIcon(Gui::BitmapFactory().iconFromTheme("Constraint_Radiam"));
8488  }
8489  break;
8490  }
8491 }

8686 
8687 void CmdSketcherConstrainAngle::activated(int iMsg)
8688 {
8689  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
8690  // TODO: comprehensive messages, like in CmdSketcherConstrainTangent
8691  // get the selection
8692  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
8693 
8694  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
8695  if (selection.size() != 1
8696  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
8697  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
8698  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
8699  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
8700 
8701  if (constraintMode) {
8702  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
8703  getSelection().clearSelection();
8704  }
8705  else {
8706  // TODO: Get the exact message from git history and put it here
8707  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument(),
8708  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8709  QObject::tr("Select the right things from the sketch."));
8710  }
8711  return;
8712  }
8713 
8714  // get the needed lists and objects
8715  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
8716  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
8717 
8718  if (SubNames.empty() || SubNames.size() > 3) {
8719  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8720  Obj,
8721  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8722  QObject::tr(
8723  "Select one or two lines from the sketch. Or select two edges and a point."));
8724  return;
8725  }
8726 
8727  int GeoId1, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId3 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
8728  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId3 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
8729  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
8730  if (SubNames.size() > 1) {
8731  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
8732  }
8733  if (SubNames.size() > 2) {
8734  getIdsFromName(SubNames[2], Obj, GeoId3, PosId3);
8735  }
8736 
8737  if (SubNames.size() == 3) {// standalone implementation of angle-via-point
8738 
8739  // let's sink the point to be GeoId3. We want to keep the order the two curves have been
8740  // selected in.
8741  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1)) {
8742  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
8743  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
8744  }
8745  if (isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
8746  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
8747  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
8748  }
8749 
8750  bool bothexternal = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
8751 
8752  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
8753 
8754  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
8755  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8756  Obj,
8757  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8758  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
8759  return;
8760  }
8761 
8762  double ActAngle = 0.0;
8763 
8764  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add angle constraint"));
8765 
8766  // add missing point-on-object constraints
8767  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
8768  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
8769  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
8770  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
8771  selection[0].getObject(),
8772  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
8773  GeoId3,
8774  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
8775  GeoId1);
8776  }
8777  }
8778  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
8779  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
8780  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
8781  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
8782  selection[0].getObject(),
8783  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
8784  GeoId3,
8785  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
8786  GeoId2);
8787  }
8788  }
8789  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
8790  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
8791  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
8792  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
8793  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
8794  selection[0].getObject(),
8795  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
8796  GeoId3,
8797  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
8798  GeoId1);
8799  }
8800  }
8801 
8802  // assuming point-on-curves have been solved, calculate the angle.
8803  // DeepSOIC: this may be slow, but I wanted to reuse the conversion
8804  // from Geometry to GCS shapes that is done in Sketch
8805  Base::Vector3d p = Obj->getPoint(GeoId3, PosId3);
8806  ActAngle = Obj->calculateAngleViaPoint(GeoId1, GeoId2, p.x, p.y);
8807 
8808  // negative constraint value avoidance
8809  if (ActAngle < -Precision::Angular()) {
8810  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
8811  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
8812  ActAngle = -ActAngle;
8813  }
8814 
8815  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
8816  selection[0].getObject(),
8817  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('AngleViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
8818  GeoId1,
8819  GeoId2,
8820  GeoId3,
8821  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
8822  ActAngle);
8823 
8824  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
8825 
8826  if (bothexternal
8827  || constraintCreationMode
8828  == Reference) {// it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
8829  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8830 
8831  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
8832  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
8833  ConStr.size() - 1,
8834  "False");
8835  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
8836  }
8837  else {
8838  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
8839  }
8840 
8841  return;
8842  }
8843  }
8844  else if (SubNames.size() < 3) {
8845 
8846  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
8847  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
8848  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
8849  }
8850 
8851  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1)
8852  || (GeoId2 != GeoEnum::GeoUndef && isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2))) {
8853  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8854  Obj,
8855  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8856  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
8857  return;
8858  }
8859 
8860  if (isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {// line to line angle
8861  makeAngleBetweenTwoLines(Obj, this, GeoId1, GeoId2);
8862  return;
8863  }
8864  else if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)) {// line angle or arc angle
8865  if (GeoId1 < 0 && GeoId1 >= Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
8866  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8867  Obj,
8868  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8869  QObject::tr("Cannot add an angle constraint on an axis!"));
8870  return;
8871  }
8872 
8873  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
8874 
8875  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
8876  auto lineSeg = static_cast<const Part::GeomLineSegment*>(geom);
8877  Base::Vector3d dir = lineSeg->getEndPoint() - lineSeg->getStartPoint();
8878  double ActAngle = atan2(dir.y, dir.x);
8879 
8880  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add angle constraint"));
8881  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
8882  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Angle',%d,%f))",
8883  GeoId1,
8884  ActAngle);
8885 
8886  if (GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
8887  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
8888  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8889 
8890  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
8891  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
8892  ConStr.size() - 1,
8893  "False");
8894  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
8895  }
8896  else {
8897  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
8898  }
8899 
8900  return;
8901  }
8902  else if (isArcOfCircle(*geom)) {
8903  auto arc = static_cast<const Part::GeomArcOfCircle*>(geom);
8904  double angle = arc->getAngle(/*EmulateCCWXY=*/true);
8905 
8906  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add angle constraint"));
8907  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
8908  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Angle',%d,%f))",
8909  GeoId1,
8910  angle);
8911 
8912  if (GeoId1 <= Sketcher::GeoEnum::RefExt || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
8913  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
8914  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
8915 
8916  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
8917  "setDriving(%d,%s)",
8918  ConStr.size() - 1,
8919  "False");
8920  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
8921  }
8922  else {
8923  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
8924  }
8925 
8926  return;
8927  }
8928  }
8929  }
8930 
8931  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8932  Obj,
8933  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8934  QObject::tr("Select one or two lines from the sketch. Or select two edges and a point."));
8935  return;
8936 }
8937 
8938 void CmdSketcherConstrainAngle::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
8939 {
8940  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
8941  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
8942  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
8943 
8944  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId3 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
8945  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none,
8946  PosId3 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
8947 
8948  switch (seqIndex) {
8949  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
8950  case 1:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
8951  case 2:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
8952  case 3:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
8953  case 4:// {SelExternalEdge, SelExternalEdge}
8954  {
8955  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
8956  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
8957 
8958  makeAngleBetweenTwoLines(Obj, this, GeoId1, GeoId2);
8959  return;
8960  }
8961  case 5:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis}
8962  case 6:// {SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
8963  case 7:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge}
8964  case 8:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge}
8965  case 9:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge}
8966  {
8967  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
8968  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
8969  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
8970  PosId3 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
8971  break;
8972  }
8973  case 10:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelEdgeOrAxis}
8974  case 11:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelEdge}
8975  case 12:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
8976  case 13:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
8977  case 14:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelExternalEdge}
8978  {
8979  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
8980  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
8981  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
8982  PosId3 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
8983  break;
8984  }
8985  }
8986 
8987  bool bothexternal = areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2);
8988 
8989  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
8990 
8991  if (isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId1) || isBsplinePole(Obj, GeoId2)) {
8992  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
8993  Obj,
8994  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
8995  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
8996  return;
8997  }
8998 
8999  double ActAngle = 0.0;
9000 
9001  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add angle constraint"));
9002 
9003  // add missing point-on-object constraints
9004  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
9005  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
9006  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
9007  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9008  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
9009  GeoId3,
9010  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
9011  GeoId1);
9012  }
9013  }
9014  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
9015  const Part::Geometry *geom2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
9016  if (!(geom2 && isBSplineCurve(*geom2))) {
9017  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9018  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
9019  GeoId3,
9020  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
9021  GeoId2);
9022  }
9023  }
9024  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId1, GeoId3, PosId3, Obj)) {
9025  // FIXME: it's a good idea to add a check if the sketch is solved
9026  const Part::Geometry *geom1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
9027  if (!(geom1 && isBSplineCurve(*geom1))) {
9028  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9029  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
9030  GeoId3,
9031  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
9032  GeoId1);
9033  }
9034  }
9035 
9036  // assuming point-on-curves have been solved, calculate the angle.
9037  // DeepSOIC: this may be slow, but I wanted to reuse the conversion
9038  // from Geometry to GCS shapes that is done in Sketch
9039  Base::Vector3d p = Obj->getPoint(GeoId3, PosId3);
9040  ActAngle = Obj->calculateAngleViaPoint(GeoId1, GeoId2, p.x, p.y);
9041 
9042  // negative constraint value avoidance
9043  if (ActAngle < -Precision::Angular()) {
9044  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
9045  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
9046  ActAngle = -ActAngle;
9047  }
9048 
9049  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9050  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('AngleViaPoint',%d,%d,%d,%d,%f))",
9051  GeoId1,
9052  GeoId2,
9053  GeoId3,
9054  static_cast<int>(PosId3),
9055  ActAngle);
9056 
9057  removeRedundantPointOnObject(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3);
9058 
9059  if (bothexternal || constraintCreationMode == Reference) {
9060  // it is a constraint on a external line, make it non-driving
9061  const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint*>& ConStr = Obj->Constraints.getValues();
9062 
9063  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj, "setDriving(%d,%s)", ConStr.size() - 1, "False");
9064  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, false);
9065  }
9066  else {
9067  finishDatumConstraint(this, Obj, true);
9068  }
9069 
9070  return;
9071  }
9072 }
9073

9116  sToolTipText =

9129 void CmdSketcherConstrainEqual::activated(int iMsg)
9130 {
9131  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
9132  // get the selection
9133  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
9134 
9135  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
9136  if (selection.size() != 1
9137  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
9138  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
9139  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
9140  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
9141 
9142  if (constraintMode) {
9143  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
9144  getSelection().clearSelection();
9145  }
9146  else {
9147  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
9148  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9149  QObject::tr("Select two edges from the sketch."));
9150  }
9151  return;
9152  }
9153 
9154  // get the needed lists and objects
9155  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
9156  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
9157 
9158  // go through the selected subelements
9159 
9160  if (SubNames.size() < 2) {
9161  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9162  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9163  QObject::tr("Select at least two lines from the sketch."));
9164  return;
9165  }
9166 
9167  std::vector<int> ids;
9168  bool lineSel = false, arcSel = false, circSel = false, ellipsSel = false, arcEllipsSel = false,
9169  hasAlreadyExternal = false;
9170  bool hyperbSel = false, parabSel = false, weightSel = false;
9171 
9172  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
9173 
9174  int GeoId;
9175  Sketcher::PointPos PosId;
9176  getIdsFromName(subname, Obj, GeoId, PosId);
9177 
9178  if (!isEdge(GeoId, PosId)) {
9179  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9180  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9181  QObject::tr("Select two or more compatible edges."));
9182  return;
9183  }
9184  else if (GeoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::HAxis || GeoId == Sketcher::GeoEnum::VAxis) {
9185  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9186  Obj,
9187  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9188  QObject::tr("Sketch axes cannot be used in equality constraints."));
9189  return;
9190  }
9191  else if (isPointOrSegmentFixed(Obj, GeoId)) {
9192 
9193  if (hasAlreadyExternal) {
9194  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9195  return;
9196  }
9197  else {
9198  hasAlreadyExternal = true;
9199  }
9200  }
9201 
9202  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId);
9203 
9204  if (isBSplineCurve(*geo)) {
9205  // unsupported as they are generally hereogeneus shapes
9206  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9207  Obj,
9208  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9209  QObject::tr("Equality for B-spline edge currently unsupported."));
9210  return;
9211  }
9212 
9213  if (isLineSegment(*geo)) {
9214  lineSel = true;
9215  }
9216  else if (isArcOfCircle(*geo)) {
9217  arcSel = true;
9218  }
9219  else if (isCircle(*geo)) {
9220  if (isBsplinePole(geo)) {
9221  weightSel = true;
9222  }
9223  else {
9224  circSel = true;
9225  }
9226  }
9227  else if (isEllipse(*geo)) {
9228  ellipsSel = true;
9229  }
9230  else if (isArcOfEllipse(*geo)) {
9231  arcEllipsSel = true;
9232  }
9233  else if (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo)) {
9234  hyperbSel = true;
9235  }
9236  else if (isArcOfParabola(*geo)) {
9237  parabSel = true;
9238  }
9239  else {
9240  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9241  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9242  QObject::tr("Select two or more edges of similar type."));
9243  return;
9244  }
9245 
9246  ids.push_back(GeoId);
9247  }
9248 
9249  // Check for heterogeneous groups in selection
9250  if ((lineSel
9251  && ((arcSel || circSel) || (ellipsSel || arcEllipsSel) || hyperbSel || parabSel || weightSel))
9252  || ((arcSel || circSel) && ((ellipsSel || arcEllipsSel) || hyperbSel || parabSel || weightSel))
9253  || ((ellipsSel || arcEllipsSel) && (hyperbSel || parabSel || weightSel))
9254  || (hyperbSel && (parabSel || weightSel)) || (parabSel && weightSel)) {
9255 
9256  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9257  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9258  QObject::tr("Select two or more edges of similar type."));
9259  return;
9260  }
9261 
9262  // undo command open
9263  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add equality constraint"));
9264  for (int i = 0; i < int(ids.size() - 1); i++) {
9265  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
9266  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Equal',%d,%d))",
9267  ids[i],
9268  ids[i + 1]);
9269  }
9270  // finish the transaction and update
9271  commitCommand();
9272  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9273 
9274  // clear the selection (convenience)
9275  getSelection().clearSelection();
9276 }
9277 
9278 void CmdSketcherConstrainEqual::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
9279 {
9280  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
9281  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
9282  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
9283 
9284  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
9285 
9286  switch (seqIndex) {
9287  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelEdge}
9288  case 1:// {SelEdge, SelExternalEdge}
9289  case 2:// {SelExternalEdge, SelEdge}
9290  {
9291  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
9292  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
9293 
9294  // check if the edge already has a Block constraint
9295  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
9296  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9297  return;
9298  }
9299 
9300  const Part::Geometry* geo1 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
9301  const Part::Geometry* geo2 = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId2);
9302 
9303  if ((isLineSegment(*geo1) && ! isLineSegment(*geo2))
9304  || (isArcOfHyperbola(*geo1) && ! isArcOfHyperbola(*geo2))
9305  || (isArcOfParabola(*geo1) && ! isArcOfParabola(*geo2))
9306  || (isBsplinePole(geo1) && !isBsplinePole(geo2))
9307  || ((isCircle(*geo1) || isArcOfCircle(*geo1)) && !(isCircle(*geo2) || isArcOfCircle(*geo2)))
9308  || ((isEllipse(*geo1) || isArcOfEllipse(*geo1)) && !(isEllipse(*geo2) || isArcOfEllipse(*geo2)))) {
9309 
9310  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9311  Obj,
9312  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9313  QObject::tr("Select two or more edges of similar type."));
9314  return;
9315  }
9316 
9317  // undo command open
9318  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add equality constraint"));
9319  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9320  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Equal',%d,%d))",
9321  GeoId1,
9322  GeoId2);
9323  // finish the transaction and update
9324  commitCommand();
9325  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9326 
9327  return;
9328  }
9329  default:
9330  break;
9331  }
9332 }

9384 void CmdSketcherConstrainSymmetric::activated(int iMsg)
9385 {
9386  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
9387  // get the selection
9388  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
9389 
9390  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
9391  if (selection.size() != 1
9392  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
9393  ParameterGrp::handle hGrp = App::GetApplication().GetParameterGroupByPath(
9394  "User parameter:BaseApp/Preferences/Mod/Sketcher");
9395  bool constraintMode = hGrp->GetBool("ContinuousConstraintMode", true);
9396 
9397  if (constraintMode) {
9398  ActivateHandler(getActiveGuiDocument(), std::make_unique<DrawSketchHandlerGenConstraint>(this));
9399  getSelection().clearSelection();
9400  }
9401  else {
9402  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9403  getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
9404  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9405  QObject::tr("Select two points and a symmetry line, "
9406  "two points and a symmetry point "
9407  "or a line and a symmetry point from the sketch."));
9408  }
9409  return;
9410  }
9411 
9412  // get the needed lists and objects
9413  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
9414  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
9415 
9416  if (SubNames.size() != 3 && SubNames.size() != 2) {
9417  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9418  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9419  QObject::tr("Select two points and a symmetry line, "
9420  "two points and a symmetry point "
9421  "or a line and a symmetry point from the sketch."));
9422  return;
9423  }
9424 
9425  int GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3;
9426  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2, PosId3;
9427  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
9428  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
9429 
9430  if (SubNames.size() == 2) {
9431  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
9432  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9433  return;
9434  }
9435  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
9436  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
9437  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
9438  }
9439  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
9440  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId1);
9441 
9442  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
9443  if (GeoId1 == GeoId2) {
9444  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9445  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9446  QObject::tr("Cannot add a symmetry constraint "
9447  "between a line and its end points."));
9448  return;
9449  }
9450 
9451  // undo command open
9452  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add symmetric constraint"));
9453  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
9454  selection[0].getObject(),
9455  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9456  GeoId1,
9457  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::start),
9458  GeoId1,
9459  static_cast<int>(Sketcher::PointPos::end),
9460  GeoId2,
9461  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
9462 
9463  // finish the transaction and update
9464  commitCommand();
9465  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9466 
9467  // clear the selection (convenience)
9468  getSelection().clearSelection();
9469  return;
9470  }
9471  }
9472 
9473  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9474  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9475  QObject::tr("Select two points and a symmetry line, "
9476  "two points and a symmetry point "
9477  "or a line and a symmetry point from the sketch."));
9478  return;
9479  }
9480 
9481  getIdsFromName(SubNames[2], Obj, GeoId3, PosId3);
9482 
9483  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9484  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId3);
9485  std::swap(PosId1, PosId3);
9486  }
9487  else if (isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9488  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
9489  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
9490  }
9491 
9492  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
9493  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9494  return;
9495  }
9496 
9497  if (isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
9498  if (isEdge(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9499  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId3);
9500 
9501  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
9502  if (GeoId1 == GeoId2 && GeoId2 == GeoId3) {
9503  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9504  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9505  QObject::tr("Cannot add a symmetry constraint "
9506  "between a line and its end points!"));
9507  return;
9508  }
9509 
9510  // undo command open
9511  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add symmetric constraint"));
9512  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
9513  selection[0].getObject(),
9514  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9515  GeoId1,
9516  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9517  GeoId2,
9518  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
9519  GeoId3);
9520 
9521  // finish the transaction and update
9522  commitCommand();
9523  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9524 
9525  // clear the selection (convenience)
9526  getSelection().clearSelection();
9527  return;
9528  }
9529  }
9530  else if (isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9531  // undo command open
9532  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add symmetric constraint"));
9533  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
9534  selection[0].getObject(),
9535  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9536  GeoId1,
9537  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9538  GeoId2,
9539  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
9540  GeoId3,
9541  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
9542 
9543  // finish the transaction and update
9544  commitCommand();
9545  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9546 
9547  // clear the selection (convenience)
9548  getSelection().clearSelection();
9549  return;
9550  }
9551  }
9552 
9553  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9554  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9555  QObject::tr("Select two points and a symmetry line, "
9556  "two points and a symmetry point "
9557  "or a line and a symmetry point from the sketch."));
9558 }
9559 
9560 void CmdSketcherConstrainSymmetric::applyConstraint(std::vector<SelIdPair>& selSeq, int seqIndex)
9561 {
9562  SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch* sketchgui =
9563  static_cast<SketcherGui::ViewProviderSketch*>(getActiveGuiDocument()->getInEdit());
9564  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj = sketchgui->getSketchObject();
9565 
9566  int GeoId1 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId2 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef, GeoId3 = GeoEnum::GeoUndef;
9567  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::none, PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::none,
9568  PosId3 = Sketcher::PointPos::none;
9569 
9570  switch (seqIndex) {
9571  case 0:// {SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot}
9572  case 1:// {SelExternalEdge, SelVertex}
9573  {
9574  GeoId1 = GeoId2 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
9575  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
9576  PosId1 = Sketcher::PointPos::start;
9577  PosId2 = Sketcher::PointPos::end;
9578  PosId3 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
9579 
9580  if (GeoId1 == GeoId3) {
9581  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9582  Obj,
9583  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9584  QObject::tr(
9585  "Cannot add a symmetry constraint between a line and its end points!"));
9586  return;
9587  }
9588 
9589  if (areBothPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2)) {
9590  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9591  return;
9592  }
9593  break;
9594  }
9595  case 2: // {SelVertex, SelEdge, SelVertexOrRoot}
9596  case 3: // {SelRoot, SelEdge, SelVertex}
9597  case 4: // {SelVertex, SelExternalEdge, SelVertexOrRoot}
9598  case 5: // {SelRoot, SelExternalEdge, SelVertex}
9599  case 6: // {SelVertex, SelEdgeOrAxis, SelVertex}
9600  case 7: // {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot,SelEdge}
9601  case 8: // {SelRoot, SelVertex, SelEdge}
9602  case 9: // {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot, SelExternalEdge}
9603  case 10:// {SelRoot, SelVertex, SelExternalEdge}
9604  case 11:// {SelVertex, SelVertex, SelEdgeOrAxis}
9605  {
9606  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
9607  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
9608  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
9609  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
9610  PosId2 = selSeq.at(2).PosId;
9611  PosId3 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
9612 
9613  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9614  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId3);
9615  std::swap(PosId1, PosId3);
9616  }
9617  else if (isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2) && isVertex(GeoId3, PosId3)) {
9618  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
9619  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
9620  }
9621 
9622  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
9623  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9624  return;
9625  }
9626 
9627  const Part::Geometry* geom = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId3);
9628 
9629  if (isLineSegment(*geom)) {
9630  if (GeoId1 == GeoId2 && GeoId2 == GeoId3) {
9631  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9632  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9633  QObject::tr("Cannot add a symmetry constraint "
9634  "between a line and its end points."));
9635  return;
9636  }
9637 
9638  // undo command open
9639  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add symmetric constraint"));
9640  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
9641  Obj,
9642  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9643  GeoId1,
9644  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9645  GeoId2,
9646  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
9647  GeoId3);
9648 
9649  // finish the transaction and update
9650  commitCommand();
9651  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9652  }
9653  else {
9654  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9655  Obj,
9656  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9657  QObject::tr("Select two points and a symmetry line, "
9658  "two points and a symmetry point "
9659  "or a line and a symmetry point from the sketch."));
9660  }
9661  return;
9662  }
9663  case 12:// {SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot, SelVertex}
9664  case 13:// {SelVertex, SelVertex, SelVertexOrRoot}
9665  case 14:// {SelVertexOrRoot, SelVertex, SelVertex}
9666  {
9667  GeoId1 = selSeq.at(0).GeoId;
9668  GeoId2 = selSeq.at(1).GeoId;
9669  GeoId3 = selSeq.at(2).GeoId;
9670  PosId1 = selSeq.at(0).PosId;
9671  PosId2 = selSeq.at(1).PosId;
9672  PosId3 = selSeq.at(2).PosId;
9673 
9674  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
9675  showNoConstraintBetweenFixedGeometry(Obj);
9676  return;
9677  }
9678  break;
9679  }
9680  default:
9681  break;
9682  }
9683 
9684  // undo command open
9685  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add symmetric constraint"));
9686  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(Obj,
9687  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Symmetric',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9688  GeoId1,
9689  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9690  GeoId2,
9691  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
9692  GeoId3,
9693  static_cast<int>(PosId3));
9694 
9695  // finish the transaction and update
9696  commitCommand();
9697 
9698  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9699 
9700  // clear the selection (convenience)
9701  getSelection().clearSelection();
9702  return;
9703 }

9725 void CmdSketcherConstrainSnellsLaw::activated(int iMsg)
9726 {
9727  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
9728 
9729  // get the selection
9730  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
9731 
9732  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
9733  if (selection.size() != 1
9734  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
9735  QString strHelp = QObject::tr("Select two endpoints of lines to act as rays, "
9736  "and an edge representing a boundary. "
9737  "The first selected point corresponds "
9738  "to index n1, second to n2, "
9739  "and the value sets the ratio n2/n1.",
9740  "Constraint_SnellsLaw");
9741 
9742  const char dmbg[] = "Constraint_SnellsLaw";
9743 
9744  QString strError = QObject::tr("Selected objects are not just geometry "
9745  "from one sketch.",
9746  dmbg);
9747 
9748  strError.append(strHelp);
9749  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
9750  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9751  std::move(strError));
9752  }
9753 
9754  // get the needed lists and objects
9755  auto* Obj = static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
9756  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
9757 
9758  if (SubNames.size() != 3) {
9759  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9760  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9761  QObject::tr("Number of selected objects is not 3"));
9762  return;
9763  }
9764 
9765  int GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3;
9766  Sketcher::PointPos PosId1, PosId2, PosId3;
9767  getIdsFromName(SubNames[0], Obj, GeoId1, PosId1);
9768  getIdsFromName(SubNames[1], Obj, GeoId2, PosId2);
9769  getIdsFromName(SubNames[2], Obj, GeoId3, PosId3);
9770 
9771  // sink the edge to be the last item
9772  if (isEdge(GeoId1, PosId1)) {
9773  std::swap(GeoId1, GeoId2);
9774  std::swap(PosId1, PosId2);
9775  }
9776  if (isEdge(GeoId2, PosId2)) {
9777  std::swap(GeoId2, GeoId3);
9778  std::swap(PosId2, PosId3);
9779  }
9780 
9781  // a bunch of validity checks
9782  if (areAllPointsOrSegmentsFixed(Obj, GeoId1, GeoId2, GeoId3)) {
9783  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9784  Obj,
9785  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9786  QObject::tr("Cannot create constraint with external geometry only."));
9787  return;
9788  }
9789 
9790  if (!(isVertex(GeoId1, PosId1) && !isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId1, PosId1)
9791  && isVertex(GeoId2, PosId2) && !isSimpleVertex(Obj, GeoId2, PosId2)
9792  && isEdge(GeoId3, PosId3))) {
9793 
9794  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9795  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9796  QObject::tr("Incompatible geometry is selected."));
9797  return;
9798  }
9799 
9800  const Part::Geometry* geo = Obj->getGeometry(GeoId3);
9801 
9802  // if (geo && isBSplineCurve(*geo)) {
9803  // // unsupported until normal to B-spline at any point implemented.
9804  // Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(
9805  // Obj,
9806  // QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9807  // QObject::tr("SnellsLaw on B-spline edge is currently unsupported."));
9808  // return;
9809  // }
9810 
9811  if (isBsplinePole(geo)) {
9812  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
9813  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9814  QObject::tr("Select an edge that is not a B-spline weight."));
9815  return;
9816  }
9817 
9818  double n2divn1 = 0;
9819 
9820  // the essence.
9821  // Unlike other constraints, we'll ask for a value immediately.
9822  QDialog dlg(Gui::getMainWindow());
9823  Ui::InsertDatum ui_Datum;
9824  ui_Datum.setupUi(&dlg);
9825  dlg.setWindowTitle(EditDatumDialog::tr("Refractive index ratio"));
9826  ui_Datum.label->setText(EditDatumDialog::tr("Ratio n2/n1:"));
9827  Base::Quantity init_val;
9828  init_val.setUnit(Base::Unit());
9829  init_val.setValue(0.0);
9830 
9831  ui_Datum.labelEdit->setValue(init_val);
9832  ui_Datum.labelEdit->setParamGrpPath(
9833  QByteArray("User parameter:BaseApp/History/SketcherRefrIndexRatio"));
9834  ui_Datum.labelEdit->setEntryName(QByteArray("DatumValue"));
9835  ui_Datum.labelEdit->setToLastUsedValue();
9836  ui_Datum.labelEdit->selectNumber();
9837  ui_Datum.labelEdit->setSingleStep(0.05);
9838  // Unable to bind, because the constraint does not yet exist
9839 
9840  if (dlg.exec() != QDialog::Accepted) {
9841  return;
9842  }
9843  ui_Datum.labelEdit->pushToHistory();
9844 
9845  Base::Quantity newQuant = ui_Datum.labelEdit->value();
9846  n2divn1 = newQuant.getValue();
9847 
9848  // add constraint
9849  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Add Snell's law constraint"));
9850 
9851  bool safe = addConstraintSafely(Obj, [&]() {
9852  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId2, GeoId1, PosId1, Obj)) {
9853  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
9854  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('Coincident',%d,%d,%d,%d))",
9855  GeoId1,
9856  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9857  GeoId2,
9858  static_cast<int>(PosId2));
9859  }
9860 
9861  if (!IsPointAlreadyOnCurve(GeoId3, GeoId1, PosId1, Obj)) {
9862  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),
9863  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('PointOnObject',%d,%d,%d))",
9864  GeoId1,
9865  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9866  GeoId3);
9867  }
9868 
9869  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(
9870  selection[0].getObject(),
9871  "addConstraint(Sketcher.Constraint('SnellsLaw',%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%.12f))",
9872  GeoId1,
9873  static_cast<int>(PosId1),
9874  GeoId2,
9875  static_cast<int>(PosId2),
9876  GeoId3,
9877  n2divn1);
9878 
9879  /*if (allexternal || constraintCreationMode==Reference) { // it is a constraint on a
9880  external line, make it non-driving const std::vector<Sketcher::Constraint *> &ConStr =
9881  Obj->Constraints.getValues();
9882 
9883  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(),"setDriving(%i,%s)",
9884  ConStr.size()-1,"False");
9885  }*/
9886  });
9887 
9888  if (!safe) {
9889  return;
9890  }
9891  else {
9892  commitCommand();
9893  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
9894  }
9895 
9896  // clear the selection (convenience)
9897  getSelection().clearSelection();
9898 }

9920 void CmdSketcherChangeDimensionConstraint::activated(int iMsg)
9921 {
9922  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
9923 
9924  auto getDimConstraint = []() {
9925  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection{getSelection().getSelectionEx()};
9926  if (selection.size() != 1 || selection[0].getSubNames().size() != 1) {
9927  throw Base::RuntimeError();
9928  }
9929 
9930  if (auto sketch = dynamic_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject())) {
9931  std::string subName = selection[0].getSubNames().at(0);
9932  if (subName.size() > 10 && subName.substr(0, 10) == "Constraint") {
9933  int ConstrId = Sketcher::PropertyConstraintList::getIndexFromConstraintName(subName);
9934  return std::make_tuple(sketch, ConstrId);
9935  }
9936  }
9937 
9938  throw Base::RuntimeError();
9939  };
9940 
9941  try {
9942  auto value = getDimConstraint();
9943  EditDatumDialog editDatumDialog(std::get<0>(value), std::get<1>(value));
9944  editDatumDialog.exec(false);
9945  }
9946  catch (const Base::RuntimeError&) {
9947  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
9948  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
9949  QObject::tr("Select one dimensional constraint from the sketch."));
9950  }

9994 void CmdSketcherToggleDrivingConstraint::updateAction(int mode)
9995 {

10001  break;

10009 void CmdSketcherToggleDrivingConstraint::activated(int iMsg)
10010 {

10013 
10014  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection;
10015 
10016  if (Gui::Selection().countObjectsOfType<Sketcher::SketchObject>() > 0) {
10017  // Now we check whether we have a constraint selected or not.
10018 
10019  // get the selection
10020  selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
10021 
10022  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
10023  if (selection.size() != 1
10024  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
10025  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
10026  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
10027  QObject::tr("Select constraints from the sketch."));
10028  return;
10029  }
10030 
10031  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj =
10032  static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
10033 
10034  // get the needed lists and objects
10035  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
10036  if (SubNames.empty()) {
10037  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
10038  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
10039  QObject::tr("Select constraints from the sketch."));
10040  return;
10041  }
10042 
10043  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
10044  // see if we have constraints, if we do it is not a mode change, but a toggle.
10045  if (subname.size() > 10 && subname.substr(0, 10) == "Constraint") {
10046  modeChange = false;
10047  }
10048  }
10049  }
10050 
10051  if (modeChange) {
10052  // Here starts the code for mode change
10053  Gui::CommandManager& rcCmdMgr = Gui::Application::Instance->commandManager();
10054 
10055  if (constraintCreationMode == Driving) {
10056  constraintCreationMode = Reference;
10057  }
10058  else {
10059  constraintCreationMode = Driving;
10060  }
10061 
10062  rcCmdMgr.updateCommands("ToggleDrivingConstraint",
10063  static_cast<int>(constraintCreationMode));
10064  }
10065  else// toggle the selected constraint(s)
10066  {
10067  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj =
10068  static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
10069 
10070  // get the needed lists and objects
10071  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
10072  if (SubNames.empty()) {
10073  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
10074  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
10075  QObject::tr("Select constraints from the sketch."));
10076  return;
10077  }
10078 
10079  // undo command open
10080  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Toggle constraint to driving/reference"));
10081 
10082  int successful = SubNames.size();
10083  // go through the selected subelements
10084  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
10085  // only handle constraints
10086  if (subname.size() > 10 && subname.substr(0, 10) == "Constraint") {
10087  int ConstrId = Sketcher::PropertyConstraintList::getIndexFromConstraintName(subname);
10088  try {
10089  // issue the actual commands to toggle
10090  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(), "toggleDriving(%d)", ConstrId);
10091  }
10092  catch (const Base::Exception&) {
10093  successful--;
10094  }
10095  }
10096  }
10097 
10098  if (successful > 0) {
10099  commitCommand();
10100  }
10101  else {
10102  abortCommand();
10103  }
10104 
10105  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
10106 
10107  // clear the selection (convenience)
10108  getSelection().clearSelection();
10109  }
10110 }

10134 void CmdSketcherToggleActiveConstraint::activated(int iMsg)
10135 {
10136  Q_UNUSED(iMsg);
10137 
10138  std::vector<Gui::SelectionObject> selection;
10139 
10140  if (Gui::Selection().countObjectsOfType<Sketcher::SketchObject>() > 0) {
10141  // Now we check whether we have a constraint selected or not.
10142 
10143  // get the selection
10144  selection = getSelection().getSelectionEx();
10145 
10146  // only one sketch with its subelements are allowed to be selected
10147  if (selection.size() != 1
10148  || !selection[0].isObjectTypeOf(Sketcher::SketchObject::getClassTypeId())) {
10149  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(getActiveGuiDocument()->getDocument(),
10150  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
10151  QObject::tr("Select constraints from the sketch."));
10152  return;
10153  }
10154 
10155  Sketcher::SketchObject* Obj =
10156  static_cast<Sketcher::SketchObject*>(selection[0].getObject());
10157 
10158  // get the needed lists and objects
10159  const std::vector<std::string>& SubNames = selection[0].getSubNames();
10160  if (SubNames.empty()) {
10161  Gui::TranslatedUserWarning(Obj,
10162  QObject::tr("Wrong selection"),
10163  QObject::tr("Select constraints from the sketch."));
10164  return;
10165  }
10166 
10167  // undo command open
10168  openCommand(QT_TRANSLATE_NOOP("Command", "Activate/Deactivate constraints"));
10169 
10170  int successful = SubNames.size();
10171 
10172  for (auto& subname : SubNames) {
10173 
10174  if (subname.size() > 10 && subname.substr(0, 10) == "Constraint") {
10175  int ConstrId = Sketcher::PropertyConstraintList::getIndexFromConstraintName(subname);
10176  try {
10177  // issue the actual commands to toggle
10178  Gui::cmdAppObjectArgs(selection[0].getObject(), "toggleActive(%d)", ConstrId);
10179  }
10180  catch (const Base::Exception&) {
10181  successful--;
10182  }
10183  }
10184  }
10185 
10186  if (successful > 0) {
10187  commitCommand();
10188  }
10189  else {
10190  abortCommand();
10191  }
10192 
10193  tryAutoRecompute(Obj);
10194 
10195  // clear the selection (convenience)
10196  getSelection().clearSelection();
10197  }
10198 }
